158void
159init_dtb(void)
160{
161 if (dtb.base == NULL) {
162 dtb.size = 480;
163 NEW(dtb.base, DTABLE, dtb.size);
164 }
165 dtb.avl = 1;
166 BZERO(dtb.base + 0, DTABLE, 1);
167}
168
169void
170free_dtb(void)
171{
172 FREE(dtb.base);
173 dtb.avl = 0;
174 dtb.size = 0;
175}
176
177static int
178mk_dtb(int which)
179{
180 int nd;
181
182 nd = dtb.avl++;
183 NEED(dtb.avl, dtb.base, DTABLE, dtb.size, dtb.size + 480);
184 if (nd > SPTR_MAX || dtb.base == NULL)
185 errfatal(7);
186 dtb.base[nd].which = which;
187 return nd;
188}

204#ifdef FLANG_DPM_OUT_UNUSED
205static void
206add_fl(int a)
207{
208 int nd;
209 int argt;
210 int ast;
211 int i;
212
213 if (!allocatable_freeing) {
214 int fr;
215 /* pghpf_free(sec) */
216 argt = mk_argt(1);
217 ARGT_ARG(argt, 0) = mk_id(a);
218 ast = mk_stmt(A_CALL, 0);
219 fr = mk_id(sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_free), DT_NONE));
220 A_LOPP(ast, fr);
221 NODESCP(A_SPTRG(A_LOPG(ast)), 1);
222 A_ARGCNTP(ast, 1);
223 A_ARGSP(ast, argt);
224 add_stmt_after(ast, ExitStd);
225 } else {
226 /* just in case, don't free more than once */
227 for (i = 0; i < fl.avl; i++)
228 if (fl.base[i] == a)
229 return;
230 nd = fl.avl++;
231 NEED(fl.avl, fl.base, int, fl.size, fl.size + 100);
232 if (nd > SPTR_MAX || fl.base == NULL)
233 errfatal(7);
234 fl.base[nd] = a;
235 }
236}
237#endif

248static void
249trans_mkproc(int sptr)
250{
251 int descr;
252 int nargs, argt, astnew;
253 int ndim, i;
254 ADSC *ad;
255
256 /* do procs descriptor */
257 descr = DESCRG(sptr);
258
259 if (VISITG(descr))
260 return;
261 VISITP(descr, 1);
262
263 /* might be scalar */
264 if (DTY(DTYPEG(sptr)) == TY_ARRAY) {
265 ndim = rank_of(DTYPEG(sptr));
266 ad = AD_DPTR(DTYPEG(sptr));
267 } else {
268 ndim = 0;
269 ad = 0;
270 }
271
272 nargs = ndim + 2;
273 argt = mk_argt(nargs);
274 ARGT_ARG(argt, 0) = mk_id(descr);
275 ARGT_ARG(argt, 1) = mk_cval(ndim, DT_INT);
276 for (i = 0; i < ndim; ++i)
277 ARGT_ARG(argt, i + 2) = mk_size(AD_LWBD(ad, i), AD_UPBD(ad, i));
278
279 astnew = mk_func_node(A_CALL,
280 mk_id(sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_processors), DT_NONE)),
281 nargs, argt);
282
283 add_stmt_before(astnew, EntryStd);
284}

286/**
287 \brief Return a 'extent(array,dim)' call
288 */
289static int
290extent(int array, int descriptor, int dimension)
291{
292 int nargs, argt, func, ast;
293 int subs[1];
294
295 if (DTYG(DTYPEG(array)) != TY_CHAR) {
296 subs[0] = mk_isz_cval(get_global_extent_index(dimension), astb.bnd.dtype);
297 ast = mk_subscr(descriptor, subs, 1, astb.bnd.dtype);
298 } else {
299 nargs = 2;
300
301 argt = mk_argt(nargs);
302 ARGT_ARG(argt, 0) = descriptor;
303 ARGT_ARG(argt, 1) = mk_isz_cval(dimension + 1, astb.bnd.dtype);
304
305 func = sym_mkfunc_nodesc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_extent), astb.bnd.dtype);
306
307 ast = mk_func_node(A_FUNC, mk_id(func), nargs, argt);
308 A_DTYPEP(ast, astb.bnd.dtype);
309 }
310 return ast;
311} /* extent */

313static void
314allocate_aligned(int sptr, int memberast, int basesptr)
315{
316 int dtype, mem;
317 if (ALLOCG(sptr))
318 return;
319 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
320 switch (DTY(dtype)) {
321 case TY_ARRAY:
322 /* may be used at internal subroutine */
323 if (SCG(basesptr) == SC_NONE && gbl.internal == 1)
324 SCP(basesptr, SC_LOCAL);
325 break;
326 case TY_DERIVED:
327 /* if this is a derived type, look at members */
328 if (POINTERG(sptr))
329 break;
330 mem = DTY(dtype + 1);
331 if (mem <= NOSYM)
332 return; /* empty derived type */
333 if (memberast) {
334 memberast = mk_member(A_PARENTG(memberast), mk_id(sptr), dtype);
335 } else {
336 memberast = mk_id(sptr);
337 }
338 /* make a A_MEM to pass to check_member */
339 memberast = mk_member(memberast, mk_id(mem), DTYPEG(mem));
340 for (; mem > NOSYM; mem = SYMLKG(mem)) {
341 if (is_tbp_or_final(mem))
342 continue; /* skip type bound procedures */
343 if (!POINTERG(mem)) {
344 allocate_aligned(mem, memberast, basesptr);
345 }
346 }
347 break;
348 }
349} /* allocate_aligned */
350
351/** Algorithm:
352 * This routine puts allocate statement for each aligned arrays except
353 * allocatable aligned arrays.
354 * allocate(a(a$sd(33):a$sd(34)))
355 * This routine is called after all pghpf_template and pghpf_instance
356 * which set array descr fully.
357 * At the end, it fixes declaration part of arrays
358 * by making the deferred array real a(:,:)
359 */
360static void
361allocate_for_aligned_array(void)
362{
363 int sptr;
364 int align;
365 int dtype;
366 ADSC *ad;
367 /* put barrier before any deallocate or copy_out if SMP */
368 /* put out allocates for local arrays */
369 for (sptr = stb.firstusym; sptr < stb.stg_avail; sptr++) {
370 switch (STYPEG(sptr)) {
371 case ST_VAR:
372 case ST_ARRAY:
373 break;
374 default:
375 continue;
376 }
377 if (IGNOREG(sptr))
378 continue;
379 allocate_aligned(sptr, 0, sptr);
380 }
381
382 /* this will fix the declaration of aligned arrays
383 * real a(:,:) instead of real a(10,10)
384 */
385 /* fix up the local arrays */
386 /* declare DYNAMIC array common */
387 for (sptr = stb.firstusym; sptr < stb.stg_avail; sptr++) {
388 int stype;
389 stype = STYPEG(sptr);
390 if (stype != ST_ARRAY)
391 continue;
392
393 /* declare DYNAMIC array pointer */
394
395 align = ALIGNG(sptr);
396 if (!align)
397 continue;
398 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY)
399 continue;
400 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
401 ad = AD_DPTR(dtype);
402 AD_DEFER(ad) = 1;
403 }
404}

406/** \brief check that distribution and alignment are mutually exclusive */
407static void
408check_flag(int flag)
409{
410 int flag1, flag2;
411
412 flag1 =
413 __PRESCRIPTIVE_ALIGN_TARGET | __DESCRIPTIVE_ALIGN_TARGET | __IDENTITY_MAP;
414 flag2 = __OMITTED_DIST_TARGET | __PRESCRIPTIVE_DIST_TARGET |
415 __DESCRIPTIVE_DIST_TARGET | __TRANSCRIPTIVE_DIST_TARGET |
416 __OMITTED_DIST_FORMAT | __PRESCRIPTIVE_DIST_FORMAT |
417 __DESCRIPTIVE_DIST_FORMAT | __TRANSCRIPTIVE_DIST_FORMAT;
418 assert(!((flag & flag1) && (flag & flag2)),
419 "check_flag: wrong flag for run-time", flag, 4);
420}
421
422static int
423construct_flag(int sptr)
424{
425 int flag;
426 flag = 0;
427 if (ASUMSZG(sptr))
428 flag |= __ASSUMED_SIZE;
429 if (SEQG(sptr))
430 flag |= __SEQUENTIAL;
431 /* set assumed-shape only if copy-in is needed. if sequential and
432 not a pointer dummy, then copy-in isn't done, but template may
433 be created */
434 if (ASSUMSHPG(sptr) && (!SEQG(sptr) || POINTERG(sptr)))
435 flag |= __ASSUMED_SHAPE;
436 if (SAVEG(sptr))
437 flag |= __SAVE;
438 /* if it is pointer */
439 if (POINTERG(sptr))
440 flag |= __POINTER;
441 if (!XBIT(47, 0x04)) {
442 if (INTENTG(sptr) == INTENT_INOUT || INTENTG(sptr) == INTENT_DFLT)
443 flag |= __INTENT_INOUT;
444 if (INTENTG(sptr) == INTENT_IN)
445 flag |= __INTENT_IN;
446 if (INTENTG(sptr) == INTENT_OUT)
447 flag |= __INTENT_OUT;
448 } else
449 flag |= __INTENT_INOUT;
450
451 check_flag(flag);
452 return flag;
453}

455static int
456make_alnd(int sptr)
457{
458 int ndim;
459 int i;
460 ADSC *ad;
461 int nd;
462 int flag;
463 int glb, gub;
464 if (is_bad_dtype(DTYPEG(sptr)))
465 return 0;
466 if ((IGNOREG(sptr) || HCCSYMG(sptr)) && DESCRG(sptr) == 0)
467 trans_mkdescr(sptr);
468 assert(DESCRG(sptr), "make_alnd: descriptor does not exist", sptr, 3);
469 if (ALNDG(DESCRG(sptr)))
470 return ALNDG(DESCRG(sptr));
471
472 nd = mk_dtb(1);
473 BZERO(dtb.base + nd, DTABLE, 1);
474 ndim = rank_of_sym(sptr);
475 TMPL_RANK(nd) = ndim;
476 TMPL_TYPE(nd) = REPLICATED;
477 flag = construct_flag(sptr);
478 TMPL_FLAG(nd) = flag;
479 {
480 ad = AD_DPTR(DTYPEG(sptr));
481
482 for (i = 0; i < ndim; ++i) {
483 /* glb */
484 glb = AD_LWBD(ad, i);
485 if (glb == 0 || A_TYPEG(glb) != A_ID || !HCCSYMG(A_SPTRG(glb)))
486 glb = AD_LWAST(ad, i);
487 if (glb == 0)
488 glb = mk_cval(1, DT_INT);
489
490 /* gub */
491 gub = AD_UPBD(ad, i);
492 if (gub == 0 || A_TYPEG(gub) != A_ID || !HCCSYMG(A_SPTRG(gub))) {
493 gub = AD_UPAST(ad, i);
494 }
495 if (gub == 0)
496 gub = mk_cval(1, DT_INT);
497
498 TMPL_LB(nd, i) = glb;
499 if (is_set(flag, __ASSUMED_SIZE) && i == ndim - 1)
500 continue;
501 if (is_set(flag, __ASSUMED_SHAPE))
502 continue;
503 TMPL_UB(nd, i) = gub;
504 }
505 }
506 return nd;
507}

509#ifdef FLANG_DPM_OUT_UNUSED
510static void
511construct_align_sc(int alnd, int alignee, int target)
512{
513 int sptr;
514 int sc, sc1;
515
516 sc = NONE_SC;
517 sptr = alignee;
518 if (ALLOCG(sptr))
519 sc = ALLOC_SC;
520 else if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_MEMBER)
521 sc = STATIC_SC;
522 else if (SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY)
523 sc = DUMMY_SC;
524 else if (SCG(sptr) == SC_CMBLK)
525 sc = COMMON_SC;
526 else if ((SCG(sptr) == SC_LOCAL || SCG(sptr) == SC_STATIC ||
527 SCG(sptr) == SC_NONE) &&
528 !ALLOCG(sptr))
529 sc = STATIC_SC;
530
531 TMPL_ALIGNEE_SC(alnd) = sc;
532
533 sc = NONE_SC;
534 sptr = target;
535 if (ALLOCG(sptr))
536 sc = ALLOC_SC;
537 else if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_MEMBER)
538 sc = STATIC_SC;
539 else if (SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY)
540 sc = DUMMY_SC;
541 else if (SCG(sptr) == SC_CMBLK)
542 sc = COMMON_SC;
543 else if ((SCG(sptr) == SC_LOCAL || SCG(sptr) == SC_STATIC ||
544 SCG(sptr) == SC_NONE) &&
545 !ALLOCG(sptr))
546 sc = STATIC_SC;
547
548 TMPL_TARGET_SC(alnd) = sc;
549
550 sc = TMPL_ALIGNEE_SC(alnd);
551 sc1 = TMPL_TARGET_SC(alnd);
552
553 /* check correctness of alignment */
554 if (sc == NONE_SC || sc1 == NONE_SC) {
555 assert(0, "construct_align_sc: wrong alignment", alignee, 3);
556 return;
557 }
558
559 if (sc == ALLOC_SC && sc1 == ALLOC_SC) {
560 return;
561 }
562 if (sc == ALLOC_SC && sc1 == DUMMY_SC) {
563 return;
564 }
565
566 if (sc == ALLOC_SC && sc1 == STATIC_SC) {
567 return;
568 }
569
570 if (sc == ALLOC_SC && sc1 == COMMON_SC) {
571 return;
572 }
573
574 if (sc == DUMMY_SC && sc1 == ALLOC_SC) {
575 /* except module allocatable */
576 if (!MDALLOCG(target))
577 error(493, 4, gbl.lineno, "Dummy", SYMNAME(alignee));
578 return;
579 }
580
581 if (sc == DUMMY_SC && sc1 == DUMMY_SC) {
582 return;
583 }
584
585 if (sc == DUMMY_SC && sc1 == STATIC_SC) {
586 return;
587 }
588
589 if (sc == DUMMY_SC && sc1 == COMMON_SC) {
590 return;
591 }
592
593 if (sc == STATIC_SC && sc1 == ALLOC_SC) {
594 /* except module allocatable */
595 if (!MDALLOCG(target))
596 error(493, 4, gbl.lineno, "Static", SYMNAME(alignee));
597 return;
598 }
599
600 if (sc == STATIC_SC && sc1 == DUMMY_SC) {
601 return;
602 }
603
604 if (sc == STATIC_SC && sc1 == STATIC_SC) {
605 return;
606 }
607
608 if (sc == STATIC_SC && sc1 == COMMON_SC) {
609 return;
610 }
611
612 if (sc == COMMON_SC && sc1 == ALLOC_SC) {
613 error(493, 3, gbl.lineno, "COMMON", SYMNAME(alignee));
614 return;
615 }
616
617 if (sc == COMMON_SC && sc1 == DUMMY_SC) {
618 error(494, 4, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(alignee), CNULL);
619 return;
620 }
621 if (sc == COMMON_SC && sc1 == STATIC_SC) {
622 return;
623 }
624
625 if (sc == COMMON_SC && sc1 == COMMON_SC) {
626 return;
627 }
628}
629#endif

641/* type: ST_ARRAY or ST_TEMPLATE */
642static void
643share_alnd(int type)
644{
645 int sptr, sptr1;
646 int arrdsc, arrdsc1;
647 int alnd, alnd1;
648 int descr;
649
650 /* make alnd */
651 for (sptr = aux.list[type]; sptr != NOSYM; sptr = SLNKG(sptr)) {
652#if DEBUG
653 /* aux.list[] must be terminated with NOSYM, not 0 */
654 assert(sptr > 0, "share_alnd: corrupted aux.list[type]", sptr, 4);
655#endif
656 arrdsc = DESCRG(sptr);
657 if (gbl.internal > 1 && !INTERNALG(sptr)) {
658 /* in a contained subprogram */
659 if (arrdsc && SDSCINITG(arrdsc) && SECDSCG(arrdsc) &&
660 SCOPEG(SECDSCG(arrdsc)) == SCOPEG(sptr) &&
661 STYPEG(SCOPEG(sptr)) != ST_MODULE)
662 continue;
663 }
664 if (ALLOCG(sptr) && (ALNDG(arrdsc) || SECDSCG(arrdsc)))
665 continue;
666 if (F90POINTERG(sptr))
667 continue;
668 alnd = make_alnd(sptr);
669 ALNDP(DESCRG(sptr), alnd);
670 }
671
672 for (sptr = aux.list[type]; sptr != NOSYM; sptr = SLNKG(sptr)) {
673#if DEBUG
674 /* aux.list[] must be terminated with NOSYM, not 0 */
675 assert(sptr > 0, "share_alnd: corrupted aux.list[type]", sptr, 4);
676#endif
677 if (is_bad_dtype(DTYPEG(sptr)))
678 continue;
679 arrdsc = DESCRG(sptr);
680 if (ALLOCG(sptr))
681 continue;
682 if (F90POINTERG(sptr))
683 continue;
684 if (gbl.internal > 1 && !INTERNALG(sptr)) {
685 if (arrdsc && SDSCINITG(arrdsc) && SECDSCG(arrdsc) &&
686 SCOPEG(SECDSCG(arrdsc)) == SCOPEG(sptr) &&
687 STYPEG(SCOPEG(sptr)) != ST_MODULE)
688 continue;
689 }
690 if (!VISITG(sptr)) {
691 descr = SECDSCG(arrdsc);
692 /* zeki descr = 0; */
693 alnd = ALNDG(arrdsc);
694 assert(alnd, "share_alnd:no alnd data structure", alnd, 3);
695 if (TMPL_DESCR(alnd) == 0) {
696 if (descr)
697 TMPL_DESCR(alnd) = descr;
698 else
699 TMPL_DESCR(alnd) = sym_get_sdescr(sptr, -1);
700 }
701 if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_MEMBER) {
702 SECDSCP(arrdsc, TMPL_DESCR(alnd));
703 }
704 VISITP(sptr, 1);
705 }
706 if (XBIT(57, 0x400000))
707 continue;
708 if (CMBLKG(sptr) && (ALIGNG(sptr) || DISTG(sptr)))
709 continue;
710 for (sptr1 = SLNKG(sptr); sptr1 != NOSYM; sptr1 = SLNKG(sptr1)) {
711 if (is_bad_dtype(DTYPEG(sptr1)))
712 continue;
713 if (SCG(sptr1) == SC_DUMMY)
714 continue;
715 if (ALLOCG(sptr1))
716 continue;
717 if (CMBLKG(sptr1) && (ALIGNG(sptr) || DISTG(sptr)))
718 continue;
719 if (STYPEG(sptr1) == ST_MEMBER && STYPEG(sptr) == ST_MEMBER) {
720 if (ENCLDTYPEG(sptr1) != ENCLDTYPEG(sptr))
721 continue;
722 if (DDTG(DTYPEG(sptr1)) != DDTG(DTYPEG(sptr)))
723 continue;
724 } else if (STYPEG(sptr1) == ST_MEMBER || STYPEG(sptr) == ST_MEMBER) {
725 continue;
726 }
727 if (!VISITG(sptr1)) {
728 if (is_same_alnd(sptr, sptr1)) {
729 arrdsc1 = DESCRG(sptr1);
730 alnd1 = ALNDG(arrdsc1);
731 if (alnd)
732 TMPL_DESCR(alnd1) = TMPL_DESCR(alnd);
733 if (STYPEG(sptr1) == ST_MEMBER) {
734 SECDSCP(arrdsc1, TMPL_DESCR(alnd1));
735 }
736 VISITP(sptr1, 1);
737 }
738 }
739 }
740 }
741 for (sptr = aux.list[type]; sptr != NOSYM; sptr = SLNKG(sptr)) {
742#if DEBUG
743 /* aux.list[] must be terminated with NOSYM, not 0 */
744 assert(sptr > 0, "share_alnd: corrupted aux.list[type]", sptr, 4);
745#endif
746 VISITP(sptr, 0);
747 }
748}
749
750LOGICAL
751is_same_alnd(int sptr, int sptr1)
752{
753 int arrdsc, arrdsc1;
754 int alnd, alnd1;
755 int ndim, ndim1;
756 int i;
757
758 arrdsc = DESCRG(sptr);
759 if (!arrdsc)
760 return FALSE;
761 arrdsc1 = DESCRG(sptr1);
762 if (!arrdsc1)
763 return FALSE;
764
765 alnd = ALNDG(arrdsc);
766 alnd1 = ALNDG(arrdsc1);
767 if (alnd == 0 && alnd1 == 0)
768 return TRUE;
769 if (alnd == 0 || alnd1 == 0)
770 return FALSE;
771
772 ndim = TMPL_RANK(alnd);
773 ndim1 = TMPL_RANK(alnd1);
774 if (ndim != ndim1)
775 return FALSE;
776
777 if (TMPL_FLAG(alnd) != TMPL_FLAG(alnd1))
778 return FALSE;
779 if (TMPL_DIST_TARGET_DESCR(alnd) != TMPL_DIST_TARGET_DESCR(alnd1))
780 return FALSE;
781 if (TMPL_ISSTAR(alnd) != TMPL_ISSTAR(alnd1))
782 return FALSE;
783 if (TMPL_CONFORM(alnd) != TMPL_CONFORM(alnd1))
784 return FALSE;
785 if (TMPL_COLLAPSE(alnd) != TMPL_COLLAPSE(alnd1))
786 return FALSE;
787 if (TMPL_ALIGN_TARGET(alnd) != TMPL_ALIGN_TARGET(alnd1))
788 return FALSE;
789 if (TMPL_TARGET_DESCR(alnd) != TMPL_TARGET_DESCR(alnd1))
790 return FALSE;
791
792 for (i = 0; i < ndim; i++) {
793 if (TMPL_LB(alnd, i) != TMPL_LB(alnd1, i))
794 return FALSE;
795 if (TMPL_UB(alnd, i) != TMPL_UB(alnd1, i))
796 return FALSE;
797 }
798
799 return TRUE;
800}
801
802LOGICAL
803is_same_secd(int sptr, int sptr1)
804{
805 int arrdsc, arrdsc1;
806 int secd, secd1;
807 int ndim, ndim1;
808
809 arrdsc = DESCRG(sptr);
810 if (!arrdsc)
811 return FALSE;
812 arrdsc1 = DESCRG(sptr1);
813 if (!arrdsc1)
814 return FALSE;
815
816 secd = SECDG(arrdsc);
817 if (!secd)
818 return FALSE;
819 secd1 = SECDG(arrdsc1);
820 if (!secd1)
821 return FALSE;
822
823 ndim = INS_RANK(secd);
824 ndim1 = INS_RANK(secd1);
825 if (ndim != ndim1)
826 return FALSE;
827 if (INS_TEMPLATE(secd) != INS_TEMPLATE(secd1))
828 return FALSE;
829 if (dtype_to_arg(DTY(DTYPEG(sptr) + 1)) !=
830 dtype_to_arg(DTY(DTYPEG(sptr1) + 1)))
831 return FALSE;
832 if (size_ast_of(mk_id(sptr), DTY(DTYPEG(sptr) + 1)) !=
833 size_ast_of(mk_id(sptr), DTY(DTYPEG(sptr1) + 1)))
834 return FALSE;
835 return TRUE;
836}

838static int
839make_secd(int sptr)
840{
841 int align;
842 int ndim;
843 int i;
844 int nolap, polap;
845 ADSC *ad;
846 int secd;
847
848 if (is_bad_dtype(DTYPEG(sptr)))
849 return 0;
850 assert(DESCRG(sptr), "make_secd: descriptor does not exist", sptr, 3);
851 secd = mk_dtb(2);
852 BZERO(dtb.base + secd, DTABLE, 1);
853 ad = AD_DPTR(DTYPEG(sptr));
854 align = ALIGNG(sptr);
855 ndim = rank_of_sym(sptr);
856
857 INS_DTYPE(secd) = DTYPEG(sptr);
858 INS_DESCR(secd) = 0;
859 INS_RANK(secd) = ndim;
860 INS_TEMPLATE(secd) = TMPL_DESCR(ALNDG(DESCRG(sptr)));
861 for (i = 0; i < ndim; ++i) {
862 nolap = 0;
863 polap = 0;
864 }
865 return secd;
866}
867
868static void
869make_secd_for_members(int dtype)
870{
871 int mem, memdtype, descr, secdsc, secd, alnd;
872
873 if (make_secd_flag[dtype])
874 return;
875 make_secd_flag[dtype] = 1;
876 for (mem = DTY(dtype + 1); mem > NOSYM; mem = SYMLKG(mem)) {
877 memdtype = DTYPEG(mem);
878 switch (DTY(memdtype)) {
879 case TY_DERIVED:
880 make_secd_for_members(memdtype);
881 break;
882 case TY_ARRAY:
883 descr = DESCRG(mem);
884 if (descr && STYPEG(descr) == ST_ARRDSC) {
885 if (DESCUSEDG(mem) || XBIT(57, 0x40000) || ALLOCG(mem)) {
886 alnd = ALNDG(descr);
887 if (!alnd) {
888 alnd = make_alnd(mem);
889 ALNDP(descr, alnd);
890 }
891 secdsc = SECDSCG(descr);
892 secd = SECDG(descr);
893 if (!secd) {
894 secd = make_secd(mem);
895 SECDP(descr, secd);
896 }
897 secdsc = SECDSCG(descr);
898 if (secdsc) {
899 INS_DESCR(secd) = secdsc;
900 INS_TEMPLATE(secd) = secdsc;
901 TMPL_DESCR(alnd) = secdsc;
902 change_mk_id(descr, secdsc);
903 } else if (INS_DESCR(secd) == 0) {
904 secdsc = sym_get_sdescr(mem, -1);
905 INS_DESCR(secd) = secdsc;
906 INS_TEMPLATE(secd) = secdsc;
907 TMPL_DESCR(alnd) = secdsc;
908 SECDSCP(descr, secdsc);
909 change_mk_id(descr, secdsc);
910 } else {
911 secdsc = INS_DESCR(secd);
912 INS_TEMPLATE(secd) = secdsc;
913 TMPL_DESCR(alnd) = secdsc;
914 SECDSCP(descr, secdsc);
915 }
916 }
917 }
918 memdtype = DTY(memdtype + 1);
919 if (DTY(memdtype) == TY_DERIVED) {
920 make_secd_for_members(memdtype);
921 }
922 break;
923 }
924 }
925} /* make_secd_for_members */
926
927/** \brief Return TRUE if we need to initialize the descriptor for this symbol
928 because perhaps this is a host subroutine, and the internal subprograms
929 will need the descriptor, or perhaps -g is set.
930 */
931LOGICAL
932want_descriptor_anyway(int sptr)
933{
934 if (gbl.internal == 1) {
935 int dtype;
936 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
937 if (DTY(dtype) != TY_ARRAY)
938 return FALSE;
939 if (!DESCRG(sptr))
940 return FALSE;
941 if (XBIT(57, 0x40000))
942 return TRUE;
943 /* descriptor for allocatable/pointer must be in host */
944 if (ALLOCG(sptr))
945 return TRUE;
946 }
947 if (flg.debug && !XBIT(123, 0x400) && !HCCSYMG(sptr) && !CCSYMG(sptr)) {
948 /* only need non-fixed bounds */
949 int dtype;
950 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
951 if (DTY(dtype) != TY_ARRAY)
952 return FALSE;
953 if (!DESCRG(sptr))
954 return FALSE;
955 if (ALIGNG(sptr) || DISTG(sptr) || ASSUMSHPG(sptr) || ALLOCG(sptr))
956 return TRUE;
957 if (ADD_DEFER(dtype) || ADD_ASSUMSHP(dtype))
958 return TRUE;
959 }
960 return FALSE;
961} /* want_descriptor_anyway */

963static void
964share_secd(void)
965{
966 int sptr, sptr1;
967 int arrdsc, arrdsc1;
968 int secd, secd1;
969 int descr;
970
971 /* make secd */
972 for (sptr = aux.list[ST_ARRAY]; sptr != NOSYM; sptr = SLNKG(sptr)) {
973 int secd;
974#if DEBUG
975 /* aux.list[] must be terminated with NOSYM, not 0 */
976 assert(sptr > 0, "share_secd: corrupted aux.list[ST_ARRAY]", sptr, 4);
977#endif
978 arrdsc = DESCRG(sptr);
979 if (gbl.internal > 1 && !INTERNALG(sptr)) {
980 if (arrdsc && SDSCINITG(arrdsc) && SECDSCG(arrdsc) &&
981 SCOPEG(SECDSCG(arrdsc)) == SCOPEG(sptr) &&
982 STYPEG(SCOPEG(sptr)) != ST_MODULE)
983 continue;
984 }
985 if (ALLOCG(sptr) && (SECDG(arrdsc) || SECDSCG(arrdsc)))
986 continue;
987 if (F90POINTERG(sptr))
988 continue;
989 secd = make_secd(sptr);
990 SECDP(arrdsc, secd);
991 }
992
993 for (sptr = aux.list[ST_ARRAY]; sptr != NOSYM; sptr = SLNKG(sptr)) {
994#if DEBUG
995 /* aux.list[] must be terminated with NOSYM, not 0 */
996 assert(sptr > 0, "share_secd: corrupted aux.list[ST_ARRAY]", sptr, 4);
997#endif
998 if (is_bad_dtype(DTYPEG(sptr)))
999 continue;
1000 arrdsc = DESCRG(sptr);
1001 if (gbl.internal > 1 && !INTERNALG(sptr)) {
1002 if (arrdsc && SDSCINITG(arrdsc) && (descr = SECDSCG(arrdsc)) &&
1003 SCOPEG(descr) == SCOPEG(sptr) && STYPEG(SCOPEG(sptr)) != ST_MODULE) {
1004 change_mk_id(arrdsc, descr);
1005 continue;
1006 }
1007 }
1008 if (ALLOCG(sptr) && (SECDG(arrdsc) == 0))
1009 continue;
1010 if (F90POINTERG(sptr))
1011 continue;
1012 if (!VISITG(sptr)) {
1013 descr = SECDSCG(arrdsc);
1014 secd = SECDG(arrdsc);
1015 if (INS_DESCR(secd) != 0)
1016 ;
1017 else if (descr)
1018 INS_DESCR(secd) = descr;
1019 else {
1020 INS_DESCR(secd) = sym_get_sdescr(sptr, -1);
1021 fix_sdsc_sc(sptr, INS_DESCR(secd), arrdsc);
1022 }
1023 change_mk_id(arrdsc, INS_DESCR(secd));
1024 VISITP(sptr, 1);
1025 }
1026 if (XBIT(57, 0x400000))
1027 continue;
1028 if (ALLOCG(sptr))
1029 continue;
1030 for (sptr1 = SLNKG(sptr); sptr1 != NOSYM; sptr1 = SLNKG(sptr1)) {
1031 if (is_bad_dtype(DTYPEG(sptr1)))
1032 continue;
1033 if (SCG(sptr1) == SC_DUMMY)
1034 continue;
1035 if (ALLOCG(sptr1))
1036 continue;
1037 if (CMBLKG(sptr1))
1038 continue;
1039 if (gbl.internal > 1 && !INTERNALG(sptr1))
1040 continue;
1041 if (!VISITG(sptr1)) {
1042 if (is_same_secd(sptr, sptr1)) {
1043 arrdsc1 = DESCRG(sptr1);
1044 secd1 = SECDG(arrdsc1);
1045 INS_DESCR(secd1) = INS_DESCR(secd);
1046 change_mk_id(arrdsc1, INS_DESCR(secd));
1047 VISITP(sptr1, 1);
1048 }
1049 }
1050 }
1051 }
1052 for (sptr = aux.list[ST_ARRAY]; sptr != NOSYM; sptr = SLNKG(sptr)) {
1053#if DEBUG
1054 /* aux.list[] must be terminated with NOSYM, not 0 */
1055 assert(sptr > 0, "share_secd: corrupted aux.list[ST_ARRAY]", sptr, 4);
1056#endif
1057 VISITP(sptr, 0);
1058 }
1059
1060 NEW(make_secd_flag, int, stb.dt.stg_avail);
1061 BZERO(make_secd_flag, int, stb.dt.stg_avail);
1062
1063 /* now handle array members in derived types */
1064 for (sptr = stb.firstosym; sptr < stb.stg_avail; sptr++) {
1065 int dtype;
1066 if (IGNOREG(sptr))
1067 continue;
1068 switch (STYPEG(sptr)) {
1069 case ST_VAR:
1070 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
1071 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_DERIVED) {
1072 make_secd_for_members(dtype);
1073 }
1074 break;
1075 case ST_ARRAY:
1076 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
1077 dtype = DTY(dtype + 1);
1078 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_DERIVED) {
1079 make_secd_for_members(dtype);
1080 }
1081 break;
1082 default:;
1083 }
1084 }
1085 if (flg.debug || (gbl.internal == 1 && XBIT(57, 0x40000))) {
1086 /* for hosts, or if debug set, initialize all members */
1087 int dtype;
1088 for (dtype = 1; dtype < stb.dt.stg_avail; dtype += dlen(DTY(dtype))) {
1089 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_DERIVED) {
1090 make_secd_for_members(dtype);
1091 }
1092 }
1093 }
1094 FREE(make_secd_flag);
1095}

1097/* MW: This used to change the A_SPTR field of the mk_id(sptr) to be sptr1.
1098 * Now it saves sptr1 in the symbol table of sptr, and puts sptr on a linked
1099 * list, so all the ASTs can be changed at once. The problem was sometimes
1100 * the change was done too early, and a subsequent mk_id of the original
1101 * sptr would be added, but not changed. */
1102
1103static int change_mk_id_list;
1104
1105static void
1106init_change_mk_id(void)
1107{
1108 change_mk_id_list = NOSYM;
1109} /* init_change_mk_id */
1110
1111static void
1112change_mk_id(int sptr, int sptr1)
1113{
1114 assert(STYPEG(sptr) == ST_ARRDSC, "change_mk_id: of non-arrdsc", STYPEG(sptr),
1115 3);
1116 if (RENAMEG(sptr) == 0) {
1117 SLNKP(sptr, change_mk_id_list);
1118 change_mk_id_list = sptr;
1119 RENAMEP(sptr, sptr1);
1120 if (flg.smp && PARREFG(sptr) && !PARREFG(sptr1)) {
1121 set_parref_flag2(sptr1, sptr, 0);
1122 }
1123 } else if (sptr1 != RENAMEG(sptr)) {
1124 assert(RENAMEG(sptr) == sptr1, "change_mk_id: arrdsc changed twice", sptr,
1125 3);
1126 }
1127} /* change_mk_id */
1128
1129static void
1130do_change_mk_id(void)
1131{
1132 int ast, sptr, sptr1, nextsptr;
1133 for (sptr = change_mk_id_list; sptr > NOSYM; sptr = nextsptr) {
1134 nextsptr = SLNKG(sptr);
1135 SLNKP(sptr, 0);
1136 sptr1 = RENAMEG(sptr);
1137 RENAMEP(sptr, 0);
1138 ast = mk_id(sptr);
1139 A_SPTRP(ast, sptr1);
1140 }
1141} /* do_change_mk_id */

1143static void
1144desc_need_arrays(void)
1145{
1146 int sptr;
1147
1148 for (sptr = stb.firstosym; sptr < stb.stg_avail; sptr++) {
1149 if (!is_array_type(sptr))
1150 continue;
1151 if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_MEMBER) {
1152 if (ALIGNG(sptr) || RUNTIMEG(sptr) || ADJARRG(sptr)) {
1153 DESCUSEDP(sptr, 1);
1154 }
1155 } else {
1156 if (SCG(sptr) != SC_NONE && ALIGNG(sptr)) {
1157 DESCUSEDP(sptr, 1);
1158 }
1159 /* may be used at internal subroutine */
1160 if (want_descriptor_anyway(sptr))
1161 DESCUSEDP(sptr, 1);
1162 }
1163 if (!DESCUSEDG(sptr))
1164 continue;
1165 if (NODESCG(sptr))
1166 continue;
1167 if (IGNOREG(sptr))
1168 continue;
1169 /* add on the list */
1170 if (SLNKG(sptr) == 0) {
1171 SLNKP(sptr, aux.list[ST_ARRAY]);
1172 aux.list[ST_ARRAY] = sptr;
1173 }
1174 }
1175}

1177static void
1178use_dummy_desc(void)
1179{
1180 int this_entry;
1181 int arg, narg;
1182 int dscptr;
1183 int i;
1184
1185 for (this_entry = gbl.entries; this_entry != NOSYM;
1186 this_entry = SYMLKG(this_entry)) {
1187 narg = PARAMCTG(this_entry);
1188 dscptr = DPDSCG(this_entry);
1189 for (i = 0; i < narg; i++) {
1190 arg = aux.dpdsc_base[dscptr];
1191 if (is_kopy_in_needed(arg))
1192 DESCUSEDP(arg, 1);
1193 dscptr++;
1194 }
1195 }

1197
1198LOGICAL
1199is_kopy_in_needed(int arg)
1200{
1201 switch (STYPEG(arg)) {
1202 default:
1203 /* procedures, labels, need no kopy in */
1204 return FALSE;
1205 case ST_VAR:
1206 case ST_ARRAY:
1207 /* only dummies, result variables passed like dummies */
1208 if (SCG(arg) != SC_DUMMY && !RESULTG(arg))
1209 return FALSE;
1210 /* pointer needs kopy-in, regardless of type */
1211 if (POINTERG(arg) || IS_PROC_DUMMYG(arg))
1212 return TRUE;
1213 /* other nonarrays need no kopy in */
1214 if (DTY(DTYPEG(arg)) != TY_ARRAY)
1215 return FALSE;
1216 /* sequential arrays need no kopy in */
1217 if (SEQG(arg)) {
1218 /* unless they WERE originally assumed-shape */
1219 int dtype;
1220 dtype = DTYPEG(arg);
1221 if (DTY(dtype) != TY_ARRAY || ADD_ASSUMSHP(dtype) != 2) {
1222 return FALSE;
1223 }
1224 }
1225 break;
1226 }
1227 /* default */
1228 return TRUE;
1229}

1241
1242/* call emit_alnd and emit_secd at subprogram entry */
1243static void
1244wrap_symbol(int sptr, int memberast, int basesptr)
1245{
1246 int mem, dtype, arrd, alloc;
1247 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
1248 alloc = 1;
1249 if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_MEMBER && want_descriptor_anyway(sptr)) {
1250 /* create for host subprogram in case used in contained routine */
1251 DESCUSEDP(sptr, 1);
1252 }
1253 switch (SCG(basesptr)) {
1254 case SC_DUMMY:
1255 /* if a dummy for this routine, and not used, skip it */
1256 if (((gbl.internal <= 1 || INTERNALG(basesptr)) && !DESCUSEDG(sptr)) ||
1257 is_kopy_in_needed(basesptr)) {
1258 return;
1259 }
1260 break;
1261 case SC_NONE:
1262 if (!DESCUSEDG(sptr))
1263 return;
1264 alloc = 0;
1265 break; /* variable isn't used, descriptor is */
1266 default:;
1267 }
1268 switch (DTY(dtype)) {
1269 case TY_ARRAY:
1270 /* if an unused symbol from the containing routine, skip it */
1271 if (gbl.internal > 1 && !INTERNALG(sptr)) {
1272 if (DESCRG(sptr) && SDSCINITG(DESCRG(sptr)) &&
1273 (arrd = SECDSCG(DESCRG(sptr))) && SCOPEG(arrd) == SCOPEG(sptr) &&
1274 STYPEG(SCOPEG(sptr)) != ST_MODULE) {
1275 return;
1276 }
1277 /* FS 2001: module array, descriptor is in the host subprogram
1278 * don't fill section descriptor in contained subprogram;
1279 * check there is a DESCR, is has an SECDSC, and its scope
1280 * is the scope of the parent of the current subpgoram */
1281 if (DESCRG(sptr) && (arrd = SECDSCG(DESCRG(sptr))) &&
1282 SCOPEG(arrd) == SCOPEG(gbl.currsub) &&
1283 STYPEG(SCOPEG(sptr)) == ST_MODULE) {
1284 change_mk_id(DESCRG(sptr), arrd);
1285 return;
1286 }
1287 }
1288 /* if a variable or array, this was handled by allocate_one_auto */
1289 if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_MEMBER && memberast) {
1290 if (ADJLENG(sptr) && alloc) {
1291 add_auto_len(sptr, EntryStd);
1292 }
1293 if (ADJARRG(sptr) || RUNTIMEG(sptr)) {
1294 (void)add_auto_bounds(sptr, EntryStd);
1295 }
1296 if (!POINTERG(sptr) && !ALLOCG(sptr) && alloc &&
1297 (ADJARRG(sptr) || RUNTIMEG(sptr) || ADJLENG(sptr))) {
1298 if (!ALIGNG(sptr) && !POINTERG(sptr)) {
1299 int ast, i, ndim, subscr[7];
1300 /* make the subscripts */
1301 ndim = ADD_NUMDIM(dtype);
1302 for (i = 0; i < ndim; ++i) {
1303 subscr[i] = mk_triple(ADD_LWAST(dtype, i), ADD_UPAST(dtype, i), 0);
1304 }
1305 ast = check_member(memberast, mk_id(sptr));
1306 mk_mem_allocate(ast, subscr, EntryStd, ast);
1307 mk_mem_deallocate(ast, ExitStd);
1308 }
1309 }
1310 }
1311 break;
1312 case TY_DERIVED:
1313 /* if this is a derived type, look at members */
1314 if (POINTERG(sptr) || is_tbp_or_final(sptr) /* skip tbp */) {
1315 return;
1316 }
1317 mem = DTY(dtype + 1);
1318 if (mem <= NOSYM)
1319 return; /* empty derived type */
1320 if (memberast) {
1321 memberast = mk_member(A_PARENTG(memberast), mk_id(sptr), dtype);
1322 } else {
1323 memberast = mk_id(sptr);
1324 }
1325 /* make a A_MEM to pass to check_member */
1326 memberast = mk_member(memberast, mk_id(mem), DTYPEG(mem));
1327 for (mem = DTY(dtype + 1); mem > NOSYM; mem = SYMLKG(mem)) {
1328 VISITP(mem, 0);
1329 }
1330 for (mem = DTY(dtype + 1); mem > NOSYM; mem = SYMLKG(mem)) {
1331 if (!POINTERG(mem) && !USELENG(mem)) /* TBD: use of length type params */
1332 wrap_symbol(mem, memberast, basesptr);
1333 }
1334 for (mem = DTY(dtype + 1); mem > NOSYM; mem = SYMLKG(mem)) {
1335 VISITP(mem, 0);
1336 }
1337 return;
1338 default:
1339 /* if an unused symbol from the containing routine, skip it */
1340 if (gbl.internal > 1 && !INTERNALG(sptr))
1341 return;
1342 if (memberast && ADJLENG(sptr) && alloc) {
1343 add_auto_len(sptr, EntryStd);
1344 if (!POINTERG(sptr) && !ALLOCG(sptr)) {
1345 /* scalar adjustable length char string */
1346 if (STYPEG(sptr) != ST_MEMBER &&
1347 (!CLASSG(sptr) || STYPEG(sptr) != ST_PROC) && /* skip tbp */
1348 EARLYSPECG(CVLENG(sptr))) {
1349 mk_allocate_scalar(memberast, sptr, STD_NEXT(EntryStd));
1350 } else {
1351 mk_allocate_scalar(memberast, sptr, EntryStd);
1352 }
1353 mk_deallocate_scalar(memberast, sptr, ExitStd);
1354 }
1355 }
1356 return;
1357 }
1358
1359 /* predefined descriptor, case like MODULE */
1360 if (DESCRG(sptr) && (arrd = SECDSCG(DESCRG(sptr))) &&
1361 (ENCLFUNCG(basesptr) || ALLOCG(sptr))) {
1362 /* allocatable HACK */
1363 change_mk_id(DESCRG(sptr), arrd);
1364 /* dynamic from module */
1365 if (ENCLFUNCG(basesptr) && STYPEG(ENCLFUNCG(basesptr)) == ST_MODULE) {
1366 if (STYPEG(arrd) == ST_DESCRIPTOR && ENCLFUNCG(arrd) == 0) {
1367 /* section descriptor is local.
1368 * For derived type members, this is true.
1369 * For non-common base symbols, this is true.
1370 * For nonhoisted common base symbols, need to initialize it.
1371 * For nondistributed common base symbols, this is true.
1372 */
1373 emit_alnd(sptr, memberast, TRUE, FALSE, 0);
1374 emit_secd(sptr, memberast, TRUE, FALSE);
1375 }
1376 }
1377 if (ENCLFUNCG(basesptr) && STYPEG(ENCLFUNCG(basesptr)) == ST_BLOCK &&
1378 ADJARRG(sptr)) {
1379 /* let it falls through */
1380 } else
1381
1382 return;
1383 }
1384
1385 /* don't generate templates for RUNTIME arrays in common */
1386 if (!ALLOCG(sptr) && !is_kopy_in_needed(basesptr) &&
1387 SCG(basesptr) != SC_CMBLK && !CCSYMG(sptr)) {
1388 emit_alnd(sptr, memberast, TRUE, FALSE, 0);
1389 emit_secd(sptr, memberast, TRUE, FALSE);
1390 SDSCINITP(DESCRG(sptr), 1);
1391 return;
1392 }
1393 /* this part is added to allow unmapped common symbols
1394 to have a descriptor */
1395 if (!ALLOCG(sptr)) {
1396 if (SCG(basesptr) == SC_CMBLK) {
1397 int cmn_sptr;
1398 cmn_sptr = CMBLKG(basesptr);
1399 if (cmn_sptr) {
1400 /* Need a descriptor for this */
1401 emit_alnd(sptr, memberast, TRUE, FALSE, 0);
1402 emit_secd(sptr, memberast, TRUE, FALSE);
1403 }
1404 }
1405 }
1406
1407} /* wrap_symbol */
1408
1409void
1410transform_wrapup(void)
1411{
1412 SPTR sptr;
1413 int this_entry;
1414 int newdsc;
1415 int exitStdNext;
1416 int saveEntryStd, saveExitStd;
1417 SPTR *wraplist;
1418 int wrapcount, routinescope_wrapcount;
1419 bool need_init;
1420 int i, j;
1421
1422 f77_local = 0;
1423 EntryStd = STD_FIRST;
1424 ExitStd = gbl.exitstd;
1425 exitStdNext = STD_NEXT(ExitStd);
1426 init_change_mk_id();
1427 use_dummy_desc();
1428 desc_need_arrays();
1429 share_alnd(ST_ARRAY);
1430 share_secd();
1431
1432 // Add user symbols to wraplist. This list is used to order calls to
1433 // wrap_symbol and related routines, which generate entry/exit code for
1434 // routine or block scope symbols. wraplist symbol order, which needs
1435 // to account for various list and code insertion reversals, is:
1436 // 1. routine scope non-earlyspec syms
1437 // 2. routine scope earlyspec syms
1438 // 3. block scope non-earlyspec syms
1439 // 4. block scope earlyspec syms
1440 NEW(wraplist, SPTR, stb.stg_avail - stb.firstosym);
1441 wrapcount = 0;
1442 for (i = 0; i <= 1; ++i) {
1443 routinescope_wrapcount = wrapcount;
1444 for (j = 0; j <= 1; ++j) {
1445 for (sptr = stb.firstosym; sptr < stb.stg_avail; ++sptr) {
1446 if (IGNOREG(sptr) || CONSTRUCTSYMG(sptr) != i || EARLYSPECG(sptr) != j)
1447 continue;
1448 switch (STYPEG(sptr)) {
1449 default:
1450 break;
1451 case ST_VAR:
1452 case ST_ARRAY:
1453 wraplist[wrapcount++] = sptr;
1454 break;
1455 case ST_MEMBER:
1456 if (DESCRG(sptr) && SECDSCG(DESCRG(sptr)) &&
1457 STYPEG(SECDSCG(DESCRG(sptr))) != ST_MEMBER)
1458 wraplist[wrapcount++] = sptr;
1459 break;
1460 }
1461 }
1462 }
1463 }
1464
1465 /* Entry arg processing and copy in/out. */
1466 for (this_entry = gbl.entries; this_entry != NOSYM;
1467 this_entry = SYMLKG(this_entry)) {
1468 unvisit_every_sptr();
1469 EntryStd = STD_NEXT(ENTSTDG(this_entry));
1470 init_fl();
1471 close_entry_guard();
1472 newdsc = newargs_for_entry(this_entry);
1473 this_entry_g = this_entry;
1474 new_dscptr_g = newdsc;
1475 /* there is an ast_visit inside interface_for_entry;
1476 * the scope of that ast_visit/ast_unvisit continues until below the
1477 * loop below */
1478 interface_for_entry(this_entry, newdsc);
1479/* keep track of which temps used for automatic array bounds have
1480 * been assigned by putting them on the A_VISIT list */
1481 for (i = 0; i < wrapcount; ++i) {
1482 sptr = wraplist[i];
1483 saveEntryStd = EntryStd;
1484 saveExitStd = ExitStd;
1485 if (CONSTRUCTSYMG(sptr)) {
1486 EntryStd = BLOCK_ENDPROLOG_STD(sptr);
1487 ExitStd = STD_PREV(BLOCK_EXIT_STD(sptr));
1488 }
1489 need_init = false;
1490 if ((gbl.internal <= 1 || INTERNALG(sptr)) && AUTOBJG(sptr))
1491 need_init = allocate_one_auto(sptr);
1492 wrap_symbol(sptr, 0, sptr);
1493 if (need_init)
1494 component_init_allocd_auto(mk_id(sptr), EntryStd);
1495
1496 /* Look for adjustable-length non-automatic character symbols. */
1497 if (STYPEG(sptr) != ST_MEMBER &&
1498 (gbl.internal <= 1 || INTERNALG(sptr)) && /* not host */
1499 (!AUTOBJG(sptr)) && /* not automatic */
1500 (!ENCLFUNCG(sptr))) { /* not module */
1501 int dty = DTYG(DTYPEG(sptr));
1502 if ((dty == TY_CHAR || dty == TY_NCHAR) && ADJLENG(sptr) &&
1503 (POINTERG(sptr) ||
1504 (ALLOCG(sptr) && !HCCSYMG(sptr) && !CCSYMG(sptr))) &&
1505 SCG(sptr) != SC_DUMMY && SCG(sptr) != SC_CMBLK) {
1506 add_auto_len(sptr, EntryStd);
1507 }
1508 }
1509
1510 /* Create MIDNUMG of dummy adjustable array here. We cannot do it
1511 * too early because there is a check in semfin, and we can't do it
1512 * in lower as it is too late for uplevel reference. */
1513 if (flg.smp && PARREFG(sptr) && SCG(sptr) != SC_DUMMY &&
1514 (ADJLENG(sptr) || AUTOBJG(sptr))) {
1515 int midnum = MIDNUMG(sptr);
1516 if (midnum == 0) {
1517 SCP(sptr, SC_BASED);
1518 midnum = sym_get_ptr(sptr);
1519 MIDNUMP(sptr, midnum);
1520 set_parref_flag2(midnum, sptr, 0);
1521 }
1522 }
1523 EntryStd = saveEntryStd;
1524 ExitStd = saveExitStd;
1525 }
1526
1527 // Don't repeat block symbol processing for secondary entry points.
1528 wrapcount = routinescope_wrapcount;
1529
1530 /* There is an ast_visit inside interface_for_entry, called above.
1531 * The scope of that ast_visit/ast_unvisit continues until here. */
1532 ast_unvisit();
1533 allocate_for_aligned_array();
1534 emit_fl();
1535 finish_fl();
1536 open_entry_guard(this_entry);
1537 if (ENTSTDG(this_entry) != EntryStd) {
1538 /* reset LINENO for any statements added at the entry point.
1539 * this allows the debugger to set its breakpoints at the proper
1540 * point, which is after the prologue code */
1541 int s;
1542 for (s = STD_NEXT(ENTSTDG(this_entry)); s != EntryStd; s = STD_NEXT(s)) {
1543 STD_LINENO(s) = 0;
1544 }
1545 }
1546 }
1547 unvisit_every_sptr();
1548 for (this_entry = gbl.entries; this_entry != NOSYM;
1549 this_entry = SYMLKG(this_entry)) {
1550 EntryStd = STD_NEXT(ENTSTDG(this_entry));
1551 declare_array_dummys(this_entry);
1552 }
1553 ExitStd = STD_PREV(exitStdNext); /* add gbi_array free stuff at end */
1554 prepare_for_astout();
1555 do_change_mk_id();
1556 free_dtb();
1557 ExitStd = EntryStd = 0;
1558 FREE(wraplist);
1559}
1560
1561/*
1562 * astout.c does not use dtb data structures
1563 */
1564static void
1565prepare_for_astout(void)
1566{
1567 int sptr;
1568 int secd, arrdsc, sdsc;
1569
1570 for (sptr = stb.firstusym; sptr < stb.stg_avail; sptr++) {
1571 if (DTY(DTYPEG(sptr)) != TY_ARRAY)
1572 continue;
1573 if (SDSCG(sptr)) {
1574 goto do_parref;
1575 continue;
1576 }
1577
1578 arrdsc = DESCRG(sptr);
1579 if (!arrdsc)
1580 continue;
1581 {
1582 if (SECDSCG(arrdsc)) {
1583 SDSCP(sptr, SECDSCG(arrdsc));
1584 } else {
1585 secd = SECDG(arrdsc);
1586 if (secd) {
1587 sdsc = INS_DESCR(secd);
1588 change_mk_id(arrdsc, sdsc);
1589 SDSCP(sptr, sdsc);
1590 SECDSCP(arrdsc, sdsc);
1591 } else if (want_descriptor_anyway(sptr) &&
1592 STYPEG(arrdsc) == ST_ARRDSC) {
1593 /* in host subprogram, or -g, make a section descriptor */
1594 sdsc = sym_get_sdescr(sptr, -1);
1595 change_mk_id(arrdsc, sdsc);
1596 SDSCP(sptr, sdsc);
1597 SECDSCP(arrdsc, sdsc);
1598 /*
1599 SHOULD CALL fix_sdsc_sc(sptr, sdsc, arrdsc); ????
1600 */
1601 }
1602 }
1603 }
1604 do_parref:
1605 if (flg.smp && PARREFG(sptr)) {
1606 int sdsc = SDSCG(sptr);
1607 if (sdsc && !PARREFG(sdsc) && DESCUSEDG(sptr)) {
1608 set_parref_flag2(sptr, 0, 0);
1609 }
1610 }
1611 }
1612 undouble_callee_args_f90();
1613 for (sptr = stb.firstusym; sptr < stb.stg_avail; sptr++) {
1614 /* clear alndp, secdp fields for array descriptors */
1615 if (DTY(DTYPEG(sptr)) != TY_ARRAY)
1616 continue;
1617 arrdsc = DESCRG(sptr);
1618 if (!arrdsc)
1619 continue;
1620 ALNDP(arrdsc, 0);
1621 SECDP(arrdsc, 0);
1622 }
1623}
1624
1625/*
1626 * The argument list was 'doubled', each argument getting its 'descriptor'
1627 * argument.
1628 * This is HPF heritage. Now we remove the unneeded descriptor arguments,
1629 * and add in REFLECTED arguments.
1630 */
1631
1632static LOGICAL arg_has_descriptor(int);
1633
1634static LOGICAL
1635pass_reflected_arg_by_value(int arg)
1636{
1637 return FALSE;
1638}
1639
1640static void
1641undouble_callee_args_f90(void)
1642{
1643 int this_entry;
1644 int dscptr, new_dscptr;
1645 int narg, orignarg, newnarg;
1646 int i;
1647 int arg, descr;
1648 int oldarg;
1649
1650 for (this_entry = gbl.entries; this_entry != NOSYM;
1651 this_entry = SYMLKG(this_entry)) {
1652 int f_descr;
1653 int istart;
1654 narg = PARAMCTG(this_entry);
1655 if (!narg)
1656 continue;
1657 orignarg = narg / 2;
1658 newnarg = 0;
1659 dscptr = DPDSCG(this_entry);
1660 new_dscptr = get_arg_table();
1661 for (i = 0; i < orignarg; i++) {
1662 int arg = aux.dpdsc_base[dscptr + i];
1663 put_arg_table(arg);
1664 newnarg++;
1665 if (pass_reflected_arg_by_value(arg))
1666 newnarg++;
1667 }
1668
1669 istart = 0;
1670 f_descr = 0;
1671 if (MVDESCG(this_entry)) {
1672 f_descr = FVALG(this_entry);
1673 if (f_descr && f_descr == aux.dpdsc_base[dscptr + 0]) {
1674 oldarg = NEWARGG(f_descr);
1675 if (arg_has_descriptor(oldarg)) {
1676 f_descr = aux.dpdsc_base[dscptr + orignarg + 0];
1677 istart = 1;
1678 }
1679 }
1680 }
1681 for (i = istart; i < orignarg; i++) {
1682 arg = aux.dpdsc_base[dscptr + i];
1683 oldarg = 0;
1684 if (arg)
1685 oldarg = NEWARGG(arg);
1686 descr = aux.dpdsc_base[dscptr + orignarg + i];
1687 if (arg_has_descriptor(oldarg)) {
1688 put_arg_table(descr);
1689 newnarg++;
1690 } else {
1691 /* change SC from DUMMY to LOCAL */
1692 if (XBIT(57, 0x10000)) {
1693 if (CLASSG(descr)) {
1694 if (STYPEG(SCOPEG(descr)) == ST_MODULE)
1695 SCP(descr, SC_EXTERN);
1696 else
1697 SCP(descr, SC_STATIC);
1698 } else
1699 SCP(descr, SC_LOCAL);
1700 }
1701 }
1702 }
1703 if (istart) {
1704 put_arg_table(f_descr);
1705 newnarg++;
1706 }
1707 PARAMCTP(this_entry, newnarg);
1708 DPDSCP(this_entry, new_dscptr);
1709 }
1710}
1711
1712static LOGICAL
1713arg_has_descriptor(int oldarg)
1714{
1715 return oldarg > NOSYM &&
1716 (ASSUMSHPG(oldarg) || POINTERG(oldarg) || IS_PROC_DUMMYG(oldarg) ||
1717 ALLOCATTRG(oldarg) || is_kopy_in_needed(oldarg));
1718}

1720void
1721emit_fl(void)
1722{
1723 int nargs, argt;
1724 int ast;
1725 int i;
1726
1727 if (fl.avl == 0)
1728 return;
1729 nargs = fl.avl + 1;
1730 argt = mk_argt(nargs);
1731 ARGT_ARG(argt, 0) = mk_cval(fl.avl, DT_INT);
1732 for (i = 0; i < fl.avl; i++) {
1733 ARGT_ARG(argt, i + 1) = mk_id(fl.base[(fl.avl - 1) - i]);
1734 }
1735 ast = mk_func_node(A_CALL, mk_id(sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_freen), DT_NONE)),
1736 nargs, argt);
1737 gbl.exitstd = add_stmt_after(ast, gbl.exitstd);
1738}
1739
1740/* if (l) then
1741 * allocate (a(1:100))
1742 * else
1743 * allocate (a(2:101))
1744 * endif
1745 */
1746
1747void
1748emit_alnd_secd(int sptr, int memberast, LOGICAL free_flag, int std,
1749 int allocbounds)
1750{
1751 int alnd, secd, ast;
1752 int old_desc, old_desc1;
1753 int savefreeing;
1754 int saveEntryStd, saveExitStd;
1755 bool tmplcall;
1756
1757 if (free_flag) {
1758 init_change_mk_id();
1759 saveEntryStd = EntryStd;
1760 saveExitStd = ExitStd;
1761 EntryStd = std;
1762 ExitStd = std;
1763 }
1764 savefreeing = allocatable_freeing;
1765 allocatable_freeing = 1;
1766 if (ALNDG(DESCRG(sptr)))
1767 old_desc = TMPL_DESCR(ALNDG(DESCRG(sptr)));
1768 else
1769 old_desc = 0;
1770 alnd = make_alnd(sptr);
1771 ALNDP(DESCRG(sptr), alnd);
1772 if (alnd) {
1773 if (SECDSCG(DESCRG(sptr)))
1774 old_desc = SECDSCG(DESCRG(sptr));
1775 if (old_desc == 0)
1776 TMPL_DESCR(alnd) = sym_get_sdescr(sptr, -1);
1777 else {
1778 TMPL_DESCR(alnd) = old_desc;
1779 VISITP(old_desc, 0);
1780 }
1781 if (free_flag)
1782 ast_visit(1, 1);
1783 tmplcall = emit_alnd(sptr, memberast, free_flag, TRUE, allocbounds);
1784 /* Copy the type length of a string array pointer from a target string
1785 array during pointer association. */
1786 ast = STD_AST(std);
1787 if (XBIT(57, 0x200000) && A_TYPEG(ast) == A_ICALL &&
1788 A_OPTYPEG(ast) == I_PTR2_ASSIGN && POINTERG(sptr)) {
1789 int target_ast, dtype;
1790 target_ast = ARGT_ARG(A_ARGSG(ast), 1);
1791 dtype = A_DTYPEG(target_ast);
1792 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY && DTY(DTY(dtype + 1)) == TY_CHAR) {
1793 /* The 5th argument to RTE_template is the type length. Pass the length
1794 if known, otherwise pass the result of a run-time LEN() call. */
1795 assert(tmplcall, "emit_alnd_secd: expected template call", 0, ERR_Fatal);
1796 if (string_length(DTY(dtype + 1)) != 0) {
1797 ARGT_ARG(A_ARGSG(STD_AST(STD_PREV(std))), 4) =
1798 mk_isz_cval(string_length(DTY(dtype + 1)), astb.bnd.dtype);
1799 } else {
1800 int sizeAst;
1801 sizeAst = sym_mkfunc_nodesc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_lena), astb.bnd.dtype);
1802 sizeAst = begin_call(A_FUNC, sizeAst, 1);
1803 add_arg(target_ast);
1804 if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_MEMBER)
1805 ARGT_ARG(A_ARGSG(STD_AST(STD_PREV(STD_PREV(std)))), 4) = sizeAst;
1806 else
1807 ARGT_ARG(A_ARGSG(STD_AST(STD_PREV(std))), 4) = sizeAst;
1808 }
1809 }
1810 }
1811 if (free_flag)
1812 ast_unvisit();
1813 /* Added second condition to `if' below.
1814 * We do not want to propagate SAVE to descriptor
1815 * if we're placing pointers in common blocks.
1816 * See also transfrm.c and astout.c.
1817 */
1818 if (SAVEG(sptr) && !POINTERG(sptr)) {
1819 SAVEP(TMPL_DESCR(ALNDG(DESCRG(sptr))), 1);
1820 if (NO_PTR || /* pointers not allowed in output */
1821 (NO_CHARPTR && DTYG(DTYPEG(sptr)) == TY_CHAR) ||
1822 (NO_DERIVEDPTR && DTYG(DTYPEG(sptr)) == TY_DERIVED))
1823 SAVEP(TMPL_DESCR(ALNDG(DESCRG(sptr))), 1);
1824 }
1825 if (GSCOPEG(sptr)) {
1826 GSCOPEP(TMPL_DESCR(ALNDG(DESCRG(sptr))), 1);
1827 }
1828 }
1829
1830 if (SECDG(DESCRG(sptr)))
1831 old_desc1 = INS_DESCR(SECDG(DESCRG(sptr)));
1832 else
1833 old_desc1 = 0;
1834 secd = make_secd(sptr);
1835 SECDP(DESCRG(sptr), secd);
1836 /* predefined descriptor, case like MODULE */
1837 if (SECDSCG(DESCRG(sptr)))
1838 old_desc1 = SECDSCG(DESCRG(sptr));
1839 if (old_desc1) {
1840 INS_DESCR(SECDG(DESCRG(sptr))) = old_desc1;
1841 VISIT2P(INS_DESCR(SECDG(DESCRG(sptr))), 0);
1842 VISIT2P(old_desc1, 0);
1843 } else if (SDSCG(sptr) && HCCSYMG(sptr)) {
1844 // If there is already a (compiler-created) SDSC, use it.
1845 INS_DESCR(SECDG(DESCRG(sptr))) = SDSCG(sptr);
1846 } else {
1847 INS_DESCR(SECDG(DESCRG(sptr))) = sym_get_sdescr(sptr, -1);
1848 }
1849 change_mk_id(DESCRG(sptr), INS_DESCR(SECDG(DESCRG(sptr))));
1850 emit_secd(sptr, memberast, free_flag, TRUE);
1851 if (SAVEG(sptr) && !POINTERG(sptr)) {
1852 SAVEP(INS_DESCR(SECDG(DESCRG(sptr))), 1);
1853 if (NO_PTR || /* pointers not allowed in output */
1854 (NO_CHARPTR && DTYG(DTYPEG(sptr)) == TY_CHAR) ||
1855 (NO_DERIVEDPTR && DTYG(DTYPEG(sptr)) == TY_DERIVED))
1856 SAVEP(INS_DESCR(SECDG(DESCRG(sptr))), 1);
1857 }
1858 if (GSCOPEG(sptr)) {
1859 GSCOPEP(INS_DESCR(SECDG(DESCRG(sptr))), 1);
1860 }
1861
1862 allocatable_freeing = savefreeing;
1863 if (free_flag) {
1864 do_change_mk_id();
1865 EntryStd = saveEntryStd;
1866 ExitStd = saveExitStd;
1867 }
1868}
1869
1870static int
1871size_of_dtype(int dtype, int sptr, int memberast)
1872{
1873 int sizeAst;
1874 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_CHAR) {
1875 /* assumed length character */
1876 if (dtype == DT_ASSCHAR || dtype == DT_DEFERCHAR) {
1877 sizeAst = sym_mkfunc_nodesc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_lena), astb.bnd.dtype);
1878 sizeAst = begin_call(A_FUNC, sizeAst, 1);
1879 add_arg(check_member(memberast, mk_id(sptr)));
1880 } else if (CVLENG(sptr) > NOSYM) {
1881 sizeAst = mk_bnd_int(mk_id(CVLENG(sptr)));
1882 } else {
1883 int clen;
1884 clen = DTY(dtype + 1);
1885 if (A_ALIASG(clen)) {
1886 sizeAst = A_ALIASG(clen);
1887 } else {
1888 sizeAst = clen;
1889 }
1890 sizeAst = mk_bnd_int(sizeAst);
1891 }
1892 } else {
1893 sizeAst = mk_isz_cval(size_of(dtype), astb.bnd.dtype);
1894 }
1895 return sizeAst;
1896}
1897
1898static void
1899emit_secd(int sptr, int memberast, LOGICAL free_flag, LOGICAL for_allocate)
1900{
1901 int secd;
1902 int arrdsc, stype, descr;
1903 int nargs, argt, astnew;
1904 int ndim;
1905 int j;
1906 int collapse;
1907 int alnd;
1908 int func;
1909 int dtype;
1910 int entryStd = EntryStd;
1911 int sizeast;
1912 int descr_ast;
1913
1914#ifdef IPA0
1915 ipa_ALN_INFO info[7];
1916#endif
1917
1918 if (is_bad_dtype(DTYPEG(sptr)))
1919 return;
1920 if (NODESCG(sptr))
1921 return;
1922 if (!DESCUSEDG(sptr))
1923 return;
1924 if (normalize_bounds(sptr) && SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY && !SEQG(sptr)) {
1925 return;
1926 }
1927
1928 arrdsc = DESCRG(sptr);
1929 assert(arrdsc > NOSYM, "emit_secd: descriptor does not exist", sptr, 3);
1930 alnd = ALNDG(arrdsc);
1931 secd = SECDG(arrdsc);
1932 /* case where array used as a template but never used as array */
1933 if (!secd)
1934 return;
1935 descr = INS_DESCR(secd);
1936 stype = STYPEG(descr);
1937 if (stype == ST_ARRDSC) {
1938 int secdsc;
1939 secdsc = SECDSCG(sptr);
1940 if (secdsc) {
1941 stype = STYPEG(secdsc);
1942 } else {
1943 stype = STYPEG(ARRAYG(sptr));
1944 }
1945 }
1946 /* don't initialize host subprogram symbols */
1947 if (!XBIT(57, 0x40000)) {
1948 if (SDSCINITG(arrdsc) && !realign && !redistribute && !for_allocate &&
1949 gbl.internal > 1 && !INTERNALG(descr) && stype != ST_MEMBER)
1950 return;
1951 } else {
1952 if (!realign && !redistribute && !for_allocate && gbl.internal > 1 &&
1953 !INTERNALG(arrdsc) && stype != ST_MEMBER)
1954 return;
1955 }
1956 ndim = INS_RANK(secd);
1957
1958 if (stype != ST_MEMBER) {
1959 if (VISIT2G(descr))
1960 return;
1961 VISIT2P(descr, 1);
1962 }
1963
1964/* void
1965 * ENTHPF(INSTANCE,instance)
1966 * (F90_Desc *dd, F90_Desc *td,
1967 * __INT_T *p_kind, __INT_T *p_len, __INT_T *p_collapse, ...)
1968 * ... = { [ __INT_T *no, __INT_T *po, ] }*
1969 */
1970 nargs = 5 + 2 * ndim + 1; /* Fix updated computation of nargs */
1971 argt = mk_argt(nargs);
1972
1973 descr_ast = check_member(memberast, mk_id(INS_DESCR(secd)));
1974 ARGT_ARG(argt, 0) = descr_ast;
1975 assert(INS_TEMPLATE(secd), "emit_secd: TEMPLATE does not exist for", sptr, 3);
1976 ARGT_ARG(argt, 1) = check_member(memberast, mk_id(INS_TEMPLATE(secd)));
1977 ARGT_ARG(argt, 2) =
1978 mk_isz_cval(dtype_to_arg(DTY(INS_DTYPE(secd) + 1)), astb.bnd.dtype);
1979
1980 dtype = DTY(INS_DTYPE(secd) + 1);
1981 sizeast = size_of_dtype(typed_alloc != DT_NONE ? typed_alloc : dtype, sptr,
1982 memberast);
1983 ARGT_ARG(argt, 3) = sizeast;
1984
1985 j = 4;
1986
1987 collapse = TMPL_COLLAPSE(alnd) | TMPL_ISSTAR(alnd);
1988 ARGT_ARG(argt, j) = mk_isz_cval(collapse, astb.bnd.dtype);
1989 j++;
1990 func = mk_id(sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_instance), DT_NONE));
1991 nargs = j;
1992 astnew = mk_func_node(A_CALL, func, nargs, argt);
1993 add_stmt_before(astnew, entryStd);
1994
1995 set_type_in_descriptor(descr_ast, sptr, typed_alloc, 0 /* no parent AST */,
1996 entryStd);
1997}
1998
1999static void
2000emit_target_alnd(int alnd, int memberast, LOGICAL free_flag)
2001{
2002 int target;
2003 int sc, sc1;
2004 int alnd1;
2005
2006 if (!TMPL_ALIGN_TARGET(alnd))
2007 return;
2008
2009 target = TMPL_ALIGN_TARGET(alnd);
2010 DESCUSEDP(target, 1);
2011 NODESCP(target, 0);
2012 sc = TMPL_ALIGNEE_SC(alnd);
2013 sc1 = TMPL_TARGET_SC(alnd);
2014
2015 /* if special case of inherited template, use the target */
2016 if (TMPL_TYPE(alnd) == INHERITED) {
2017 NODESCP(target, 1);
2018 return;
2019 }
2020
2021 if (sc == ALLOC_SC && sc1 == ALLOC_SC) {
2022 alnd1 = ALNDG(DESCRG(target));
2023 assert(alnd, "emit_target_alnd: misplaced ALLOCATABLE alignment", target,
2024 3);
2025 TMPL_TARGET_DESCR(alnd) = TMPL_DESCR(alnd1);
2026 return;
2027 }
2028 if (sc == ALLOC_SC && sc1 == DUMMY_SC) {
2029 TMPL_TARGET_DESCR(alnd) = DESCRG(target);
2030 return;
2031 }
2032
2033 if (sc == ALLOC_SC && sc1 == STATIC_SC) {
2034 /* static target (template) must be handled by
2035 * handle_nonalloc_template
2036 */
2037 TMPL_TARGET_DESCR(alnd) = DESCRG(target);
2038 return;
2039 }
2040 if (sc == ALLOC_SC && sc1 == COMMON_SC) {
2041 TMPL_TARGET_DESCR(alnd) = DESCRG(target);
2042 return;
2043 }
2044 if (sc == DUMMY_SC && sc1 == ALLOC_SC) {
2045 if (MDALLOCG(target))
2046 TMPL_TARGET_DESCR(alnd) = SECDSCG(DESCRG(target));
2047 else
2048 assert(0, "emit_target_alnd: wrong alignment", target, 3);
2049 return;
2050 }
2051 if (sc == DUMMY_SC && sc1 == DUMMY_SC) {
2052 /* if this is for a CALL statement, the dummy arguments
2053 * are processed in reverse order, don't need to recurse here */
2054 emit_kopy_in(target, this_entry_g, 0);
2055 TMPL_TARGET_DESCR(alnd) = TMPL_DESCR(ALNDG(DESCRG(target)));
2056 return;
2057 }
2058 if (sc == DUMMY_SC && sc1 == STATIC_SC) {
2059 emit_alnd(target, memberast, free_flag, FALSE, 0);
2060 TMPL_TARGET_DESCR(alnd) = TMPL_DESCR(ALNDG(DESCRG(target)));
2061 return;
2062 }
2063 if (sc == DUMMY_SC && sc1 == COMMON_SC) {
2064 TMPL_TARGET_DESCR(alnd) = TMPL_DESCR(ALNDG(DESCRG(target)));
2065 return;
2066 }
2067 if (sc == STATIC_SC && sc1 == ALLOC_SC) {
2068 if (MDALLOCG(target))
2069 TMPL_TARGET_DESCR(alnd) = SECDSCG(DESCRG(target));
2070 else
2071 assert(0, "emit_target_alnd: wrong alignment", target, 3);
2072 return;
2073 }
2074 if (sc == STATIC_SC && sc1 == DUMMY_SC) {
2075 if (!TMPL_DESCR(ALNDG(DESCRG(target))))
2076 emit_kopy_in(target, this_entry_g, 0);
2077 TMPL_TARGET_DESCR(alnd) = TMPL_DESCR(ALNDG(DESCRG(target)));
2078 return;
2079 }
2080 if (sc == STATIC_SC && sc1 == STATIC_SC) {
2081 emit_alnd(target, memberast, free_flag, FALSE, 0);
2082 TMPL_TARGET_DESCR(alnd) = TMPL_DESCR(ALNDG(DESCRG(target)));
2083 return;
2084 }
2085 if (sc == STATIC_SC && sc1 == COMMON_SC) {
2086 emit_alnd(target, memberast, free_flag, FALSE, 0);
2087 TMPL_TARGET_DESCR(alnd) = TMPL_DESCR(ALNDG(DESCRG(target)));
2088 return;
2089 }
2090 if (sc == COMMON_SC && sc1 == ALLOC_SC) {
2091 assert(0, "emit_target_alnd: wrong alignment", target, 3);
2092 return;
2093 }
2094 if (sc == COMMON_SC && sc1 == DUMMY_SC) {
2095 assert(0, "emit_target_alnd: wrong alignment", target, 3);
2096 return;
2097 }
2098 if (sc == COMMON_SC && sc1 == STATIC_SC) {
2099 emit_alnd(target, memberast, free_flag, FALSE, 0);
2100 TMPL_TARGET_DESCR(alnd) = TMPL_DESCR(ALNDG(DESCRG(target)));
2101 return;
2102 }
2103 if (sc == COMMON_SC && sc1 == COMMON_SC) {
2104 emit_alnd(target, memberast, free_flag, FALSE, 0);
2105 TMPL_TARGET_DESCR(alnd) = TMPL_DESCR(ALNDG(DESCRG(target)));
2106 return;
2107 }
2108 assert(0, "emit_target_alnd: something is wrong with dist", target, 3);
2109}

2111/** \brief Scan an expression for compiler-created symbols.
2112 \return
2113 + 0 if the expression contains a compiler-created symbol
2114 + 1 if all variables are user declared
2115 + -1 if all symbols are constants (or something other than above)
2116
2117 We use this routine when examining the distribution block factor
2118 expression.
2119
2120 */
2121int
2122find_cc_symbols(int ast)
2123{
2124 int rslt = -1, k;
2125
2126 k = A_TYPEG(ast);
2127
2128 if (k) {
2129
2130 if (k == A_UNOP || k == A_BINOP) {
2131
2132 if (A_TYPEG(A_LOPG(ast))) {
2133 rslt = find_cc_symbols(A_LOPG(ast));
2134 if (!rslt)
2135 return 0;
2136 }
2137
2138 if (A_TYPEG(A_ROPG(ast))) {
2139 int rslt_right;
2140
2141 rslt_right = find_cc_symbols(A_ROPG(ast));
2142
2143 if (!rslt_right)
2144 return 0;
2145 else if (rslt_right == 1)
2146 rslt = 1;
2147 }
2148 } else if (k == A_ID) {
2149 int j;
2150
2151 j = A_SPTRG(ast);
2152 if (CCSYMG(j) || HCCSYMG(j))
2153 return 0;
2154 else
2155 return 1;
2156 }
2157 }
2158
2159 return rslt;
2160}

2162void
2163set_typed_alloc(DTYPE t)
2164{
2165 /* used to pass the type into emit_alnd() when it's called via typed
2166 * allocation statement (e.g., allocate(type-spec::object) )
2167 */
2168 typed_alloc = t;
2169}
2170
2171/*
2172 * Set the type in a descriptor to a DTYPE, if known, or to the
2173 * run-time type of a symbol. The type is set by calling the
2174 * run-time library routine RTE_set_type or RTE_set_intrin_type
2175 * as appropriate.
2176 */
2177void
2178set_type_in_descriptor(int descriptor_ast, int sptr, DTYPE dtype0,
2179 int parent_ast, int before_std)
2180{
2181 DTYPE dtype = dtype0;
2182 int tag_sptr, dtype_arg_ast, type_ast = 0;
2183 FtnRtlEnum func = RTE_no_rtn;
2184
2185 if (dtype == DT_NONE && sptr > NOSYM)
2186 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
2187 if (is_array_dtype(dtype))
2188 dtype = array_element_dtype(dtype);
2189
2190 tag_sptr = get_struct_tag_sptr(dtype);
2191 if (tag_sptr > NOSYM || is_unl_poly(sptr)) {
2192 /* polymorphic or derived type */
2193 func = RTE_set_type;
2194 if (tag_sptr > NOSYM && !UNLPOLYG(tag_sptr)) {
2195 /* known monomorphic derived type */
2196 int typedsc_sptr = get_static_type_descriptor(tag_sptr);
2197 if (typedsc_sptr > NOSYM)
2198 type_ast = mk_id(typedsc_sptr);
2199 }
2200 if (type_ast == 0 && sptr > NOSYM && (CLASSG(sptr) || FINALIZEDG(sptr))) {
2201 type_ast = find_descriptor_ast(sptr, parent_ast);
2202 if (type_ast == 0) {
2203 int typedsc_sptr = get_static_type_descriptor(sptr);
2204 if (typedsc_sptr > NOSYM)
2205 type_ast = mk_id(typedsc_sptr);
2206 }
2207 }
2208 } else if ((dtype_arg_ast = dtype_to_arg(dtype)) > 0) {
2209 /* intrinsic type */
2210 func = RTE_set_intrin_type;
2211 type_ast = mk_unop(OP_VAL, mk_cval1(dtype_arg_ast, DT_INT), DT_INT);
2212 }
2213
2214 if (type_ast > 0 && type_ast != descriptor_ast) {
2215 int argt = mk_argt(2), astnew;
2216 int func_ast = mk_id(sym_mkfunc_nodesc(mkRteRtnNm(func), DT_NONE));
2217 ARGT_ARG(argt, 0) = descriptor_ast;
2218 ARGT_ARG(argt, 1) = (SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY && CLASSG(sptr)) ?
2219 mk_id(get_type_descr_arg(gbl.currsub, sptr)) : type_ast;
2220 astnew = mk_func_node(A_CALL, func_ast, 2, argt);
2221 add_stmt_before(astnew, before_std);
2222 }
2223}
2224
2225/*
2226 * void
2227 * pghpf_template
2228 * (distr **template, __INT4_T *rank, __INT4_T *flags, ...)
2229 * ... = [ [ proc *dist_target, ]
2230 * __INT4_T *isstar,
2231 * { __INT4_T *blocks, }* ]p
2232 *
2233 * [ section *align_target, __INT4_T *conform,
2234 * [ __INT4_T *collapse,
2235 * { __INT4_T *axis, __INT4_T *stride, __INT4_T *offset, }*
2236 * __INT4_T *single,
2237 * { __INT4_T *coordinate, }* ] ]
2238 * { __INT4_T *lb,
2239 * [ __INT4_T *ub, ] }*
2240 */
2241static bool
2242emit_alnd(int sptr, int memberast, LOGICAL free_flag, LOGICAL for_allocate,
2243 int allocbounds)
2244{
2245 int alnd;
2246 int arrdsc, stype;
2247 int nargs, argt, astnew, cargs;
2248 int ndim;
2249 int func, descr;
2250 int realign1, redistribute1;
2251 int proc, proc_descr;
2252 int entryStd = EntryStd;
2253
2254 if (is_bad_dtype(DTYPEG(sptr)))
2255 return false;
2256 if (NODESCG(sptr))
2257 return false;
2258 if (!DESCUSEDG(sptr))
2259 return false;
2260 if (normalize_bounds(sptr) && SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY && !SEQG(sptr)) {
2261 return false;
2262 }
2263
2264 arrdsc = DESCRG(sptr);
2265 assert(arrdsc, "emit_alnd: descriptor does not exist", sptr, 3);
2266 alnd = ALNDG(arrdsc);
2267 assert(alnd, "emit_alnd: TEMPLATE does not exist", sptr, 3);
2268 ndim = TMPL_RANK(alnd);
2269
2270 descr = TMPL_DESCR(alnd);
2271 stype = STYPEG(descr);
2272 if (stype == ST_ARRDSC) {
2273 int secdsc;
2274 secdsc = SECDSCG(sptr);
2275 if (secdsc) {
2276 stype = STYPEG(secdsc);
2277 } else {
2278 stype = STYPEG(ARRAYG(sptr));
2279 }
2280 }
2281
2282 /* don't have to initialize descriptors for host subprogram symbols */
2283 if (SDSCINITG(arrdsc) && !realign && !redistribute && !for_allocate &&
2284 gbl.internal > 1 && !INTERNALG(descr) && stype != ST_MEMBER)
2285 return false;
2286
2287 if (VISITG(descr))
2288 return false;
2289 VISITP(descr, 1);
2290
2291 /* don't call recursively pghpf_realign and pghpf_redistribute */
2292 realign1 = realign;
2293 redistribute1 = redistribute;
2294 realign = 0;
2295 redistribute = 0;
2296
2297 /* get target descriptor */
2298 if (TMPL_ALIGN_TARGET(alnd)) {
2299 emit_target_alnd(alnd, memberast, free_flag);
2300 assert(TMPL_TARGET_DESCR(alnd), "emit_alnd: no descriptor exist", sptr, 3);
2301 }
2302
2303 proc = TMPL_DIST_TARGET(alnd);
2304 proc_descr = TMPL_DIST_TARGET_DESCR(alnd);
2305 if (proc_descr) {
2306 trans_mkproc(proc);
2307 }
2308
2309 nargs = 8 + 6 * ndim + 9 + 7;
2310 cargs = 0;
2311 if (XBIT(57, 0x200000))
2312 nargs += 2; /* two more arguments for kind/len */
2313 argt = mk_argt(nargs);
2314 ARGT_ARG(argt, cargs++) = check_member(memberast, mk_id(TMPL_DESCR(alnd)));
2315 ARGT_ARG(argt, cargs++) = mk_isz_cval(TMPL_RANK(alnd), astb.bnd.dtype);
2316 ARGT_ARG(argt, cargs++) = mk_isz_cval(TMPL_FLAG(alnd), astb.bnd.dtype);
2317 if (XBIT(57, 0x200000)) { /* leave room for kind/len */
2318 ARGT_ARG(argt, cargs++) = mk_isz_cval(0, astb.bnd.dtype);
2319 ARGT_ARG(argt, cargs++) = mk_isz_cval(0, astb.bnd.dtype);
2320 }
2321 nargs = fill_argt_with_alnd(sptr, memberast, argt, alnd, cargs, redistribute1,
2322 allocbounds);
2323
2324 if (redistribute1)
2325 func = mk_id(sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_redistribute), DT_NONE));
2326 else if (realign1)
2327 func = mk_id(sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_realign), DT_NONE));
2328 else {
2329
2330 /*
2331 * If the blocking factor is set by a user declared variable,
2332 * we need to generate a call to pghpf_check_block_size to
2333 * insure that the block size >= 1 ...
2334 *
2335 * We generate a call to pghpf_check_block_size if all variables
2336 * in the blocking factor expression are user declared. If there
2337 * are any compiler created variables, then we do not generate
2338 * the call. Also we do not generate the call if the expression
2339 * contains all constants.
2340 */
2341
2342 if (XBIT(57, 0x200000)) {
2343 func = mk_id(sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_template), DT_NONE));
2344 } else {
2345 func = mk_id(sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_templateDsc), DT_NONE));
2346 }
2347 }
2348 astnew = mk_func_node(A_CALL, func, nargs, argt);
2349 add_stmt_before(astnew, entryStd);
2350
2351 /* Set the type in the descriptor for a derived type member. */
2352 if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_MEMBER)
2353 set_type_in_descriptor(check_member(memberast, mk_id(TMPL_DESCR(alnd))),
2354 sptr, typed_alloc, 0 /* no parent AST */, entryStd);
2355
2356 return true;
2357}

2362 /* call pgf90_temp_desc(tmp desc, orig desc) */
2363 SPTR sptr_descr;

2387
2388static int
2389fill_argt_with_alnd(int sptr, int memberast, int argt, int alnd, int j,
2390 int redist, int allocbounds)
2391{
2392 int i;
2393 int sptrTarg, tmpl_descr;
2394 int ndim;
2395 int flag;
2396 int asd;
2397
2398 ndim = TMPL_RANK(alnd);
2399
2400 if (memberast && A_TYPEG(memberast) == A_SUBSCR)
2401 memberast = A_LOPG(memberast);
2402 if (!memberast || A_TYPEG(memberast) != A_MEM)
2403 memberast = 0;
2404
2405 if (memberast) {
2406 int s, a, dt, m;
2407 if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_MEMBER && memberast) {
2408 s = MIDNUMG(sptr);
2409 if (s) {
2410 a = mk_id(s);
2411 ast_replace(a, check_member(memberast, a));
2412 }
2413 s = PTROFFG(sptr);
2414 if (s) {
2415 a = mk_id(s);
2416 ast_replace(a, check_member(memberast, a));
2417 }
2418 }
2419 /* any members of the same datatype might have SDSC fields */
2420 m = A_MEMG(memberast);
2421 dt = ENCLDTYPEG(A_SPTRG(m));
2422 for (m = DTY(dt + 1); m > NOSYM; m = SYMLKG(m)) {
2423 s = SDSCG(m);
2424 if (s) {
2425 a = mk_id(s);
2426 ast_replace(a, check_member(memberast, a));
2427 }
2428 }
2429 }
2430
2431 if (TMPL_DIST_TARGET_DESCR(alnd)) {
2432 ARGT_ARG(argt, j) = check_member(
2433 memberast, ast_rewrite(mk_id(TMPL_DIST_TARGET_DESCR(alnd))));
2434 j++;
2435 }
2436
2437 flag = TMPL_FLAG(alnd);
2438 if (TMPL_TYPE(alnd) == DISTRIBUTED &&
2439 ((getbits(flag, DIST_FORMAT_SHIFT, 2) == PRESCRIP) ||
2440 (getbits(flag, DIST_FORMAT_SHIFT, 2) == DESCRIP))) {
2441 ARGT_ARG(argt, j) = mk_isz_cval(TMPL_ISSTAR(alnd), astb.bnd.dtype);
2442 j++;
2443 }
2444
2445 sptrTarg = TMPL_ALIGN_TARGET(alnd);
2446 if (sptrTarg) {
2447 tmpl_descr = TMPL_TARGET_DESCR(alnd);
2448 ARGT_ARG(argt, j) = check_member(memberast, ast_rewrite(mk_id(tmpl_descr)));
2449 j++;
2450 }
2451
2452 if (TMPL_CONFORM(alnd)) {
2453 ARGT_ARG(argt, j) = TMPL_CONFORM(alnd);
2454 j++;
2455 }
2456
2457 if (!is_set(TMPL_FLAG(alnd), __IDENTITY_MAP) && TMPL_TYPE(alnd) == ALIGNED) {
2458 ARGT_ARG(argt, j) = mk_isz_cval(TMPL_COLLAPSE(alnd), astb.bnd.dtype);
2459 j++;
2460 }
2461
2462 if (allocbounds) {
2463 assert(A_TYPEG(allocbounds) == A_SUBSCR, "fill_argt: expecting subscript",
2464 A_TYPEG(allocbounds), 4);
2465 asd = A_ASDG(allocbounds);
2466 assert(ASD_NDIM(asd) == ndim, "fill_argt: dimensionality doesn't match",
2467 ASD_NDIM(asd), 4);
2468 }
2469 for (i = 0; i < ndim; ++i) {
2470 int ast;
2471
2472 if (allocbounds) {
2473 /* this is the A_SUBSCR with the bounds */
2474 int triplet, stride;
2475 triplet = ASD_SUBS(asd, i);
2476 assert(A_TYPEG(triplet) == A_TRIPLE,
2477 "fill_argt: expecting triplet in allocate subscript",
2478 A_TYPEG(triplet), 4);
2479
2480 /* Power: create lb and ub temps to avoid a gcc bug where a register was
2481 * not being updated after calls to mk_bnd_int, resulting in storing the
2482 * result in the old (now reallocated via mk_argt) astb.argt structure.
2483 * See: FS21905.
2484 */
2485 if ((stride = A_STRIDEG(triplet)) != 0 && A_TYPEG(stride) == A_CNST &&
2486 ad_val_of(A_SPTRG(stride)) < 0) {
2487 const int ub = mk_bnd_int(A_UPBDG(triplet));
2488 const int lb = mk_bnd_int(A_LBDG(triplet));
2489 ARGT_ARG(argt, j) = ub;
2490 j++;
2491 ARGT_ARG(argt, j) = lb;
2492 j++;
2493 } else {
2494 const int lb = mk_bnd_int(A_LBDG(triplet));
2495 const int ub = mk_bnd_int(A_UPBDG(triplet));
2496 ARGT_ARG(argt, j) = lb;
2497 j++;
2498 ARGT_ARG(argt, j) = ub;
2499 j++;
2500 }
2501 } else {
2502 if (TMPL_LB(alnd, i)) {
2503 ast =
2504 mk_bnd_int(check_member(memberast, ast_rewrite(TMPL_LB(alnd, i))));
2505 if (normalize_bounds(sptr))
2506 ast = astb.bnd.one;
2507 ARGT_ARG(argt, j) = ast;
2508 j++;
2509 }
2510 if (TMPL_UB(alnd, i)) {
2511 ast =
2512 mk_bnd_int(check_member(memberast, ast_rewrite(TMPL_UB(alnd, i))));
2513 if (normalize_bounds(sptr)) {
2514 ast = mk_binop(OP_SUB, ast,
2515 check_member(memberast, ast_rewrite(TMPL_LB(alnd, i))),
2516 astb.bnd.dtype);
2517 ast = mk_binop(OP_ADD, ast, astb.bnd.one, astb.bnd.dtype);
2518 }
2519 ARGT_ARG(argt, j) = ast;
2520 j++;
2521 }
2522 }
2523 }
2524 return j;
2525}

2527/* These two routines(get_arg_table and pur_arg_table) are
2528 * to get new arg list dscptr and put arg into list
2529 * is used to create new entry arg list such as:
2530 * interface; function func(a,b)
2531 */
2532static int
2533get_arg_table(void)
2534{
2535 return aux.dpdsc_avl;
2536}
2537
2538static void
2539put_arg_table(int arg)
2540{
2541 NEED(aux.dpdsc_avl + 1, aux.dpdsc_base, int, aux.dpdsc_size,
2542 aux.dpdsc_size + 100);
2543 *(aux.dpdsc_base + (aux.dpdsc_avl++)) = arg;
2544}
2545
2546/* This will create new variables for subroutine interface.
2547 * subroutine foo(array1, scalar1) will have new four new variables
2548 * subroutine foo(actual_array1, actual_scalar1, sec_array1, sec_scalar1)
2549 * This will be written at above format. The new variables is also stored
2550 * inti aux.dpdsc axuliary data structure. It stores first actual variables
2551 * and then section descriptor. It will return the base address of this
2552 * new dpdsc which have 2*narg element. That will be stored into
2553 * ST_ENTRYs DPDSC and PARAMCT by interface_for_entry.
2554 */
2555
2556static int
2557newargs_for_entry(int this_entry)
2558{
2559 int dscptr;
2560 int arg, narg;
2561 int i;
2562 int formal;
2563 int new_dscptr;
2564 int newarg, newdsc;
2565
2566 narg = PARAMCTG(this_entry);
2567 dscptr = DPDSCG(this_entry);
2568 new_dscptr = get_arg_table();
2569 for (i = 0; i < narg; i++) {
2570 arg = aux.dpdsc_base[dscptr];
2571 if (arg == 0) {
2572 formal = 0;
2573 } else if (STYPEG(arg) != ST_ARRAY && STYPEG(arg) != ST_VAR &&
2574 !IS_PROC_DUMMYG(arg)) {
2575 formal = arg;
2576 } else {
2577 newarg = NEWARGG(arg);
2578 newdsc = NEWDSCG(arg);
2579 if (normalize_bounds(arg)) {
2580 if (newarg == arg) {
2581 if (needs_redim(arg))
2582 /* ...create new dummy symbol. */
2583 newarg = 0;
2584 } else {
2585 if (!needs_redim(arg))
2586 /* ...don't create new symbol. */
2587 newarg = arg;
2588 }
2589 }
2590 if (!F90POINTERG(arg) &&
2591 ((is_array_type(arg) && !is_bad_dtype(DTYPEG(arg))) ||
2592 POINTERG(arg) || ALLOCATTRG(arg) || IS_PROC_DUMMYG(arg))) {
2593 /* use the address field to hold new name for param/section */
2594 formal = newarg;
2595 if (XBIT(57, 0x80000) && (formal == arg || formal == 0) &&
2596 (POINTERG(arg) || ALLOCATTRG(arg) || IS_PROC_DUMMYG(arg))) {
2597 if (MIDNUMG(arg)) {
2598 SCP(MIDNUMG(arg), SC_DUMMY);
2599 OPTARGP(MIDNUMG(arg), OPTARGG(arg));
2600 }
2601 if (formal == 0)
2602 formal = arg;
2603 }
2604 if (!formal)
2605 formal = sym_get_formal(arg);
2606 newarg = formal;
2607 NEWARGP(newarg, arg);
2608 NEWDSCP(newarg, 0);
2609 } else
2610 formal = arg;
2611 NEWARGP(arg, newarg);
2612 NEWDSCP(arg, newdsc);
2613 }
2614 put_arg_table(formal);
2615 dscptr++;
2616 }
2617 dscptr = DPDSCG(this_entry);
2618 for (i = 0; i < narg; i++) {
2619 arg = aux.dpdsc_base[dscptr];
2620 if (arg == 0) {
2621 newdsc = sym_get_sec("alt", 1);
2622 } else {
2623 newdsc = NEWDSCG(arg);
2624 if (newdsc == 0) {
2625 set_preserve_descriptor(CLASSG(arg) || is_procedure_ptr(arg) ||
2626 (sem.which_pass && IS_PROC_DUMMYG(arg)) ||
2627 (ALLOCDESCG(arg) && RESULTG(arg)));
2628 newdsc = sym_get_arg_sec(arg);
2629 if (!ALLOCDESCG(arg) && RESULTG(arg)) {
2630 /* Make sure the result has the updated descriptor in its SDSC
2631 * field. It's needed when setting up arguments for the function
2632 * callee. Also the ADDRESS field overloads NEWDSC which gets reset in
2633 * lower_visit_symbol() of lowersym.c for function results.
2634 */
2635 SDSCP(arg, newdsc);
2636 }
2637 set_preserve_descriptor(0);
2638 NEWDSCP(arg, newdsc);
2639 }
2640 }
2641 if (XBIT(54, 0x40) && CONTIGATTRG(arg)
2642 && STYPEG(newdsc) != ST_UNKNOWN
2643 ) {
2644 /* Generate contiguity check on this argument.
2645 *
2646 * NOTE: For LLVM targets, this function gets called by
2647 * newargs_for_llvmiface() to set up placeholder descriptor
2648 * arguments in the interface. We do not want to
2649 * generate contiguity checks in this case since an interface
2650 * block is non-executable code. The sym_get_arg_sec() function
2651 * above returns a newdsc without any STYPE when we're processing
2652 * an interface. Therefore, we check whether STYPEG(newdsc) != ST_UNKNOWN.
2653 */
2654 int ast = mk_id(arg);
2655 gen_contig_check(ast, ast, newdsc, FUNCLINEG(gbl.currsub), false,
2656 EntryStd);
2657 }
2658 SCP(newdsc, SC_DUMMY);
2659 OPTARGP(newdsc, OPTARGG(arg));
2660 NEWARGP(newdsc, 0);
2661 NEWDSCP(newdsc, 0);
2662 NEED(aux.dpdsc_avl + 1, aux.dpdsc_base, int, aux.dpdsc_size,
2663 aux.dpdsc_size + 100);
2664 aux.dpdsc_base[aux.dpdsc_avl++] = newdsc;
2665 dscptr++;
2666 }
2667 INTERFACEP(this_entry, 1);
2668 return new_dscptr;
2669}

2671#ifdef FLANG_DPM_OUT_UNUSED
2672/* This routine generate IFTHEN to test static descriptor
2673 * initilaized. "if(a$sd(1) .eq. 0)
2674 */
2675static int
2676exist_test(int sdsc, int memberast)
2677{

2679 int astnew;

2682 subs[0] = mk_cval(1, astb.bnd.dtype);

2691
2692static int *orderargs; /* List of arguments in dependence order. */
2693
2694/*
2695 * Algorithm:
2696 * subroutine foo(a)
2697 * integer a(100)
2698 * will be transformed.
2699 *
2700 * subroutine foo(array_b, array_b_sec) ! called actual in the code
2701 * integer a(:) ! called arg in the code
2702 * integer array_b(1)
2703 * integer array_b_sec(1)
2704 * pointer (a_p, a)
2705 * a_sect_p = pghpf_newsect(...
2706 * ...
2707 * a_p = pghpf_copy_in(array_b, a_sec, array_b_sec)
2708 * redimension(a(..))
2709 * ...
2710 * pghpf_copy_out(array_b, a, array_b_sec, array_a_sec)
2711 *
2712 * non-sequential common blocks will be transformed as well.
2713 *
2714 * add_adjarr_bounds calls add_bound_assignments, which keeps track of
2715 * which temps have already been assigned by putting them on the A_VISIT list.
2716 */
2717
2718static void
2719interface_for_entry(int this_entry, int new_dscptr)
2720{
2721 int arg, narg;
2722 int i;
2723 int argnum, dscptr;
2724
2725 narg = PARAMCTG(this_entry);
2726 dscptr = DPDSCG(this_entry);
2727 this_entry_fval = FVALG(this_entry);
2728
2729 if (narg) {
2730 NEW(orderargs, int, narg);
2731 reorder_args(this_entry);
2732 }
2733 /* the scope of this ast_visit/ast_unvisit continues past the return
2734 * from interface_for_entry to the caller, transform_wrapup */
2735 ast_visit(1, 1);
2736
2737 for (i = 0; i < narg; i++) {
2738 argnum = orderargs[i];
2739 arg = aux.dpdsc_base[dscptr + argnum];
2740 if (STYPEG(arg) != ST_ARRAY && STYPEG(arg) != ST_VAR)
2741 continue;
2742 if (!f77_local && DTY(DTYPEG(arg)) == TY_ARRAY)
2743 add_adjarr_bounds(arg);
2744 if (ADJLENG(arg)) {
2745 add_auto_len(arg, EntryStd);
2746 }
2747 if (normalize_bounds(arg)) {
2748 if (needs_redim(arg))
2749 emit_redim(arg);
2750 } else
2751 emit_kopy_in(arg, this_entry, 0);
2752 }
2753
2754 if (narg) {
2755 FREE(orderargs);
2756 PARAMCTP(this_entry, 2 * narg);
2757 DPDSCP(this_entry, new_dscptr);
2758 }
2759}
2760
2761/* Return TRUE if the bounds of sptrA are dependent on sptrB, or the bounds
2762 * of sptrB. */
2763static LOGICAL
2764bounds_depends(int sptrA, int sptrB)
2765{
2766 int astB, astBnd;
2767 ADSC *adA, *adB;
2768 int ndimsA, dimA, ndimsB, dimB;
2769 int sptrSD, fval;
2770
2771 if (DTY(DTYPEG(sptrA)) != TY_ARRAY)
2772 return FALSE;
2773 if (!ADJARRG(sptrA))
2774 return FALSE;
2775 astB = mk_id(sptrB);
2776 ndimsB = 0;
2777 if (DTY(DTYPEG(sptrB)) == TY_ARRAY) {
2778 adB = AD_DPTR(DTYPEG(sptrB));
2779 ndimsB = AD_NUMDIM(adB);
2780 }
2781 adA = AD_DPTR(DTYPEG(sptrA));
2782 ndimsA = AD_NUMDIM(adA);
2783 for (dimA = 0; dimA < ndimsA; dimA++) {
2784 if (contains_ast(AD_LWBD(adA, dimA), astB) ||
2785 contains_ast(AD_UPBD(adA, dimA), astB))
2786 return TRUE;
2787 for (dimB = 0; dimB < ndimsB; dimB++) {
2788 astBnd = AD_LWAST(adB, dimB);
2789 if (A_TYPEG(astBnd) == A_ID) {
2790 if (astBnd != AD_LWBD(adA, dimA) &&
2791 contains_ast(AD_LWBD(adA, dimA), astBnd))
2792 return TRUE;
2793 if (astBnd != AD_UPBD(adA, dimA) &&
2794 contains_ast(AD_UPBD(adA, dimA), astBnd))
2795 return TRUE;
2796 }
2797 astBnd = AD_UPAST(adB, dimB);
2798 if (A_TYPEG(astBnd) == A_ID) {
2799 if (astBnd != AD_LWBD(adA, dimA) &&
2800 contains_ast(AD_LWBD(adA, dimA), astBnd))
2801 return TRUE;
2802 if (astBnd != AD_UPBD(adA, dimA) &&
2803 contains_ast(AD_UPBD(adA, dimA), astBnd))
2804 return TRUE;
2805 }
2806 }
2807 }
2808 switch (STYPEG(sptrB)) {
2809 case ST_ARRAY:
2810 sptrSD = SDSCG(sptrB);
2811 if (sptrSD && bounds_depends(sptrA, sptrSD))
2812 return TRUE;
2813 break;
2814 default:;
2815 }
2816 switch (STYPEG(sptrA)) {
2817 case ST_ARRAY:
2818 return FALSE;
2819 case ST_PROC:
2820 fval = FVALG(sptrA);
2821 return fval && bounds_depends(fval, sptrB);
2822 default:
2823 return FALSE;
2824 }
2825}
2826
2827/* return TRUE if the bounds or alignment of isptr depends on jsptr */
2828static LOGICAL
2829arg_depends(int isptr, int jsptr)
2830{
2831 int aln, dst;
2832 if (bounds_depends(isptr, jsptr)) {
2833 return TRUE;
2834 }
2835 aln = 0;
2836 dst = 0;
2837 return FALSE;
2838} /* arg_depends */
2839
2840/* Reorder arguments to procedure sptrEntry, adding to the list beginning
2841 * at *orderargs. Argument A will come before argument B if B's bounds
2842 * are dependent on A's bounds, B is aligned with A, or A came originally
2843 * before B in the argument list. */
2844static void
2845reorder_args(int sptrEntry)
2846{
2847 int nargs, iargnum, jargnum, iarg, jarg, isptr, jsptr;
2848 int dscptr;
2849 int cycle;
2850
2851 nargs = PARAMCTG(sptrEntry);
2852 dscptr = DPDSCG(sptrEntry);
2853
2854 /* we are sorting a partial order;
2855 * the arguments may come in the order ( a b c d e f )
2856 * with dependences: (where c<a means c must precede a)
2857 * c<a<e
2858 * Even a bubble sort can fail */
2859 for (iargnum = 0; iargnum < nargs; ++iargnum) {
2860 orderargs[iargnum] = iargnum;
2861 }
2862 cycle = 0;
2863 for (iargnum = 0; iargnum < nargs;) {
2864 /* we know 'iargnum' can follow all previous arguments. */
2865 /* see if it must follow any subsequent argument */
2866 iarg = orderargs[iargnum];
2867 isptr = aux.dpdsc_base[dscptr + iarg];
2868 for (jargnum = iargnum + 1; jargnum < nargs; ++jargnum) {
2869 jarg = orderargs[jargnum];
2870 jsptr = aux.dpdsc_base[dscptr + jarg];
2871 if (!jsptr)
2872 continue;
2873 if (arg_depends(isptr, jsptr)) {
2874 /* isptr must follow jsptr */
2875 /* swap iarg and jarg, restart for jarg */
2876 orderargs[iargnum] = jarg;
2877 orderargs[jargnum] = iarg;
2878 break;
2879 }
2880 }
2881 if (jargnum == nargs) {
2882 /* isptr is ok where it is */
2883 ++iargnum;
2884 cycle = 0; /* isptr is not involved in a cycle */
2885 } else {
2886 ++cycle; /* see if we have a dependence cycle */
2887 if (cycle > nargs) {
2888 /* quit */
2889 error(498, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(jsptr), CNULL);
2890 ++iargnum;
2891 }
2892 }
2893 }
2894} /* reorder_args */
2895
2896/* Produce a REDIMENSION statement for the array whose symbol table pointer
2897 * is arg within the procedure given by this_entry. */
2898static void
2899emit_redim(int arg)
2900{
2901 int p_sptr;
2902 int newarg;
2903 int present;
2904 int astnew;
2905
2906 newarg = NEWARGG(arg);
2907 assert(newarg, "emit_redim: no newarg", arg, 4);
2908
2909 p_sptr = MIDNUMG(arg);
2910 if (!p_sptr)
2911 p_sptr = get_array_pointer(arg);
2912
2913 if (OPTARGG(arg)) {
2914 present = sym_mkfunc_nodesc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_present), stb.user.dt_log);
2915 present = ast_intr(I_PRESENT, stb.user.dt_log, 1, mk_id(newarg));
2916 astnew = mk_stmt(A_IFTHEN, 0);
2917 A_IFEXPRP(astnew, present);
2918 add_stmt_before(astnew, EntryStd);
2919 gbitable.unconditional = 0;
2920 }
2921
2922 if (!POINTERG(arg)) {
2923 redimension(arg, 0);
2924
2925 /* Assign the location of the parameter to the array's pointer. */
2926 astnew = ast_intr(I_LOC, DT_INT, 1, mk_id(newarg));
2927 astnew = mk_assn_stmt(mk_id(p_sptr), astnew, DT_ADDR);
2928 add_stmt_before(astnew, EntryStd);
2929 }
2930
2931 if (OPTARGG(arg)) {
2932 astnew = mk_stmt(A_ENDIF, 0);
2933 add_stmt_before(astnew, EntryStd);
2934 gbitable.unconditional = 1;
2935 }
2936}
2937
2938/** \brief Return TRUE if the array with symbol table pointer arg requires a
2939 redimension statement. */
2940LOGICAL
2941needs_redim(int arg)
2942{
2943 int newarg;
2944 int dtyp;
2945
2946 if (arg != 0)
2947 newarg = NEWARGG(arg);
2948 else
2949 newarg = 0;
2950 if (newarg == 0)
2951 return FALSE;
2952 if (SCG(arg) != SC_DUMMY)
2953 return FALSE;
2954 if (!is_array_type(arg))
2955 return FALSE;
2956 if (is_bad_dtype(DTYPEG(arg)))
2957 return FALSE;
2958 if (f77_local)
2959 return FALSE;
2960 if (!DESCRG(arg) || !SECDSCG(DESCRG(arg)))
2961 return FALSE;
2962 if (NO_PTR || (NO_CHARPTR && DTYG(DTYPEG(arg)) == TY_CHAR) ||
2963 (NO_DERIVEDPTR && DTYG(DTYPEG(arg)) == TY_DERIVED))
2964 /* ...Cray pointers not allowed. */
2965 return FALSE;
2966 dtyp = DDTG(DTYPEG(arg));
2967 if (dtyp == DT_ASSNCHAR || dtyp == DT_ASSCHAR || dtyp == DT_DEFERCHAR ||
2968 dtyp == DT_DEFERCHAR)
2969 /* ...can't redimension assumed length character arrays. */
2970 return FALSE;
2971 if (ASSUMSHPG(arg))
2972 return TRUE;
2973 if (SEQG(arg))
2974 return FALSE;
2975 return TRUE;
2976}
