2978/*
2979 * pghpf_kopy_in
2980 * (char **dbase, section **dsect, char *abase, section *asect,
2981 * __INT4_T *rank, __INT4_T *kind, __INT4_T *size, __INT4_T *flags, ...)
2982 * ... = [ [ proc *dist_target, ]
2983 * __INT4_T *isstar,
2984 * { __INT4_T *blocks, }* ]
2985 * [ section *align_target, __INT4_T *conform,
2986 * [ __INT4_T *collapse,
2987 * { __INT4_T *axis, __INT4_T *stride, __INT4_T *offset, }*
2988 * __INT4_T *single,
2989 * { __INT4_T *coordinate, }* ] ]
2990 * { __INT4_T *lb,
2991 * [ __INT4_T *ub, ]
2992 * [ __INT4_T *no, __INT4_T *po, ] }*
2993 */
2994static void
2995emit_kopy_in(int arg, int this_entry, int actual)
2996{
2997
2998 int dscptr;
2999 int narg;
3000 int dummy_sec;
3001 int nargs, argt;
3002 int astnew, ast;
3003 int p_sptr, o_sptr;
3004 int asn;
3005 int newarg, newdsc;
3006 int arrdsc;
3007 int alnd, secd;
3008 int proc, proc_descr;
3009 int collapse;
3010 int ndim;
3011 int flag;
3012 int present;
3013 int pointerAst;
3014 int offsetAst;
3015 int baseAst, srcAst;
3016 int dtype;
3017 int is_kopy_out_needed;
3018
3019 if (F90POINTERG(arg))
3020 return;
3021 if (POINTERG(arg) && XBIT(57, 0x80000))
3022 return;
3023 /* scalar pointer handling */
3024 if (POINTERG(arg) && DTY(DTYPEG(arg)) != TY_ARRAY) {
3025 emit_scalar_kopy_in(arg, this_entry);
3026 return;
3027 }
3028
3029 narg = PARAMCTG(this_entry);
3030 dscptr = DPDSCG(this_entry);
3031 if (arg != 0) {
3032 newarg = NEWARGG(arg);
3033 newdsc = NEWDSCG(arg);
3034 } else
3035 newarg = newdsc = 0;
3036 if (newarg == 0)
3037 return;
3038 if (newdsc) {
3039 newdsc = check_member(actual, mk_id(newdsc));
3040 }
3041 if (!is_array_type(arg))
3042 return;
3043 if (is_bad_dtype(DTYPEG(arg)))
3044 return;
3045
3046 if (!f77_local) {
3047 if (!DESCUSEDG(arg))
3048 return;
3049 if (!is_kopy_in_needed(arg))
3050 return;
3051 if (XBIT(57, 0x10000) && SCG(arg) == SC_DUMMY && !POINTERG(arg))
3052 return;
3053 }
3054
3055 assert(DTY(DTYPEG(arg)) == TY_ARRAY && !is_bad_dtype(DTYPEG(arg)),
3056 "interface_for_entry: bad arg type", arg, 4);
3057 DESCUSEDP(arg, 1);
3058 dummy_sec = INS_DESCR(SECDG((DESCRG(arg))));
3059 arrdsc = DESCRG(arg);
3060 alnd = ALNDG(arrdsc);
3061 assert(alnd, "emit_kopy_in: TEMPLATE does not exist", arg, 3);
3062 secd = SECDG(arrdsc);
3063 assert(secd, "emit_kopy_in: not array", arg, 3);
3064 if (VISITG(TMPL_DESCR(alnd)))
3065 return;
3066 if (VISIT2G(INS_DESCR(secd)))
3067 return;
3068 VISITP(TMPL_DESCR(alnd), 1);
3069 VISIT2P(INS_DESCR(secd), 1);
3070 change_mk_id(DESCRG(arg), INS_DESCR(secd));
3071 is_kopy_out_needed = !SEQG(arg) || POINTERG(arg) || f77_local;
3072
3073 /* if it is optional dummy */
3074 if (OPTARGG(arg) && !f77_local) {
3075 /* just to declare it */
3076
3077 /*
3078 * Changed:
3079 * present = sym_mkfunc_nodesc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_present),DT_LOG);
3080 * present = ast_intr(I_PRESENT, DT_LOG, 1, mk_id(newarg));
3081 */
3082
3083 present = sym_mkfunc_nodesc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_present), stb.user.dt_log);
3084 present = ast_intr(I_PRESENT, stb.user.dt_log, 1, mk_id(newarg));
3085 astnew = mk_stmt(A_IFTHEN, 0);
3086 A_IFEXPRP(astnew, present);
3087 add_stmt_before(astnew, EntryStd);
3088 gbitable.unconditional = 0;
3089 }
3090
3091 /* if it is optional dummy */
3092 if (OPTARGG(arg) && !f77_local && is_kopy_out_needed) {
3093 astnew = mk_stmt(A_ENDIF, 0);
3094 add_stmt_after(astnew, ExitStd);
3095 }
3096
3097 /* make sure processor descriptor created */
3098 proc = TMPL_DIST_TARGET(alnd);
3099 proc_descr = TMPL_DIST_TARGET_DESCR(alnd);
3100 if (proc_descr) {
3101 trans_mkproc(proc);
3102 }
3103
3104 /* pghpf_kopy_in creates only one descriptor */
3105 TMPL_DESCR(ALNDG((DESCRG(arg)))) = dummy_sec;
3106
3107 /* make sure that, align_target is set before alignee */
3108 /* get target descriptor */
3109 if (TMPL_ALIGN_TARGET(alnd)) {
3110 emit_target_alnd(alnd, 0, TRUE);
3111 assert(TMPL_TARGET_DESCR(alnd), "emit_kopy_in: no descriptor", arg, 3);
3112 }
3113
3114 ndim = TMPL_RANK(alnd);
3115 nargs = 8 + 2 + 9 * ndim + 9 + 7;
3116 argt = mk_argt(nargs);
3117 dtype = DTY(INS_DTYPE(secd) + 1);
3118
3119 /* pointer to arg */
3120 p_sptr = 0;
3121 if ((normalize_bounds(arg) || SEQG(arg)) && !f77_local)
3122 if (POINTERG(arg))
3123 p_sptr = get_array_pointer(arg);
3124 else
3125 p_sptr = 0;
3126 else {
3127 if (f77_local && MIDNUMG(arg))
3128 p_sptr = MIDNUMG(arg);
3129 else
3130 p_sptr = get_array_pointer(arg);
3131 }
3132
3133 o_sptr = PTROFFG(arg);
3134
3135 if (NO_PTR || (NO_CHARPTR && DTYG(DTYPEG(arg)) == TY_CHAR) ||

3627/*
3628 * subtract difference between actual and dummy lower bounds
3629 * ast - locallower + globallower
3630 * special cases if ast == locallower or locallower == globallower
3631 */
3632static int
3633diff_lbnd(int dtyp, int dim, int ast, int descr)
3634{
3635 int ast1;
3636 int astBnd = ADD_LWAST(dtyp, dim);
3637 int astglb = get_global_lower(descr, dim);
3638
3639 if (astBnd == astglb)
3640 return ast;
3641
3642 if (astBnd == ast)
3643 return astglb;
3644 ast1 = ast;
3645 if (astBnd)
3646 astglb = mk_binop(OP_SUB, astglb, astBnd, astb.bnd.dtype);
3647 ast1 = mk_binop(OP_ADD, ast1, astglb, astb.bnd.dtype);
3648 return ast1;
3649} /* diff_lbnd */
3650
3651/** \brief Create section descriptor and initialize prior to call.
3652
3653 It initialize before std. And section information comes from AST arr.
3654 \p ast is A_SUBSCR with non-null shape.
3655 To find section boundary, it looks for AST. If AST is not enough
3656 (e.g, `A(:,1)`), it uses the shape. Check for `A(:)%%B(5)` also.
3657 */
3658int
3659make_sec_from_ast(int ast, int std, int stdafter, int sec_ast, int sectflag)
3660{
3661 int sec;
3662
3663 sec = make_sec_from_ast_chk(ast, std, stdafter, sec_ast, sectflag, 0);
3664 return sec;
3665}
3666
3667int
3668make_sec_from_ast_chk(int ast, int std, int stdafter, int sec_ast, int sectflag,
3669 int ignore_c)
3670{
3671 int a, arr, sec;
3672 int descr;
3673 int nargs, argt, astnew;
3674 int ndim, numdim;
3675 int i, j, dim_mask;
3676 int glb, gub, gst;
3677 int asd;
3678 int triple;
3679 int sptr, fsptr;
3680 int shape;
3681 int subs[7];
3682 LOGICAL rhs_is_dist;
3683 int bogus;
3684 int strd1_cnt;
3685
3686 /* find the array that has the section */
3687 arr = 0;
3688 for (a = ast; a != 0;) {
3689 switch (A_TYPEG(a)) {
3690 case A_SUBSCR:
3691 /* it must have a shape; its parent
3692 * must be an A_ID, or an A_MEM whose parent has no shape */
3693 if (!A_SHAPEG(a)) {
3694 arr = a; /* probably an error */
3695 a = 0;
3696 } else {
3697 int lop;
3698 lop = A_LOPG(a);
3699 if (A_TYPEG(lop) == A_ID) {
3700 arr = a;
3701 a = 0;
3702 } else if (A_TYPEG(lop) == A_MEM) {
3703 int parent;
3704 parent = A_PARENTG(lop);
3705 if (A_SHAPEG(parent)) {
3706 a = parent;
3707 } else {
3708 arr = a;
3709 a = 0;
3710 }
3711 } else {
3712 interr("make_sec_from_ast: invalid A_SUBSCR parent", A_TYPEG(lop), 4);
3713 }
3714 }
3715 break;
3716 case A_MEM:
3717 a = A_PARENTG(a);
3718 break;
3719 case A_ID:
3720 default:
3721 a = 0;
3722 break;
3723 }
3724 }
3725 if (arr == 0 || A_TYPEG(arr) != A_SUBSCR) {
3726 interr("make_sec_from_ast: no subscript", ast, 2);
3727 return 0;
3728 }
3729
3730 /* localize section, for example a(idx1(1), idx1(2):idx2(7)) */
3731 asd = A_ASDG(arr);
3732 numdim = ASD_NDIM(asd);
3733 if (!pure_gbl.local_mode) {
3734 int sptr, dtype;
3735 for (i = 0; i < numdim; ++i) {
3736 rhs_is_dist = FALSE;
3737 subs[i] = get_scalar_in_expr(ASD_SUBS(asd, i), std, TRUE);
3738 /*insert_comm_before(std, ASD_SUBS(asd, i), &rhs_is_dist, TRUE);*/
3739 }
3740 sptr = sptr_of_subscript(arr);
3741 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
3742 arr = mk_subscr(A_LOPG(arr), subs, numdim, dtype);
3743 }
3744 shape = A_SHAPEG(arr);
3745 assert(shape != 0, "make_sec_from_ast: shape null", 0, 4);
3746 /* create a section descriptor */
3747 sptr = sptr_of_subscript(arr);
3748 bogus = getbit(sectflag, 8);
3749 if (is_whole_array(arr) && !bogus) {
3750 DESCUSEDP(sptr, 1);
3751 return DESCRG(sptr);
3752 }
3753 if (sec_ast == 0) {
3754 sec = sym_get_sdescr(sptr, SHD_NDIM(shape)); /* ZB */
3755 sec_ast = mk_id(sec);
3756 } else {
3757 sec = NOSYM;
3758 }
3759 descr = DESCRG(sptr);
3760 ndim = rank_of(DTYPEG(sptr));
3761 nargs = 4 + 3 * ndim;
3762 /* RTE_sect(descr,olddesct,rank,l1,u2,s1,...,lN,uN,sN) */
3763 argt = mk_argt(nargs);
3764 nargs = 0;
3765 ARGT_ARG(argt, nargs++) = sec_ast;
3766 DESCUSEDP(sptr, 1);
3767 ARGT_ARG(argt, nargs++) = check_member(A_LOPG(arr), mk_id(descr));
3768 gst = mk_isz_cval(ndim, astb.bnd.dtype);
3769 ARGT_ARG(argt, nargs++) = mk_bnd_int(gst);
3770 asd = A_ASDG(arr);
3771 numdim = ASD_NDIM(asd);
3772 assert(numdim == ndim, "make_sec_from_ast: numdim from asd", sptr, 3);
3773 j = SHD_NDIM(shape) - 1;
3774 dim_mask = 0;
3775 strd1_cnt = 0;
3776 for (i = ndim - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
3777 dim_mask <<= 1;
3778 if (A_TYPEG(triple = ASD_SUBS(asd, i)) == A_TRIPLE) {
3779 assert(j >= 0, "make_sec_from_ast: SHD/ASD mismatch", arr, 4);
3780 glb = SHD_LWB(shape, j);
3781 gub = SHD_UPB(shape, j);
3782 gst = SHD_STRIDE(shape, j);
3783 --j;
3784 dim_mask |= 1; /* vector dimension */
3785 } else {
3786 glb = ASD_SUBS(asd, i);
3787 gub = glb;
3788 gst = mk_isz_cval(1, astb.bnd.dtype);
3789 }
3790 glb = mk_bnd_int(glb);
3791 gub = mk_bnd_int(gub);
3792 if (ASSUMSHPG(sptr) && XBIT(57, 0x10000)) {
3793 /* offset by difference between actual/dummy lower bounds */
3794 glb = diff_lbnd(DTYPEG(sptr), i, glb, descr);
3795 gub = diff_lbnd(DTYPEG(sptr), i, gub, descr);
3796 }
3797 ARGT_ARG(argt, 3 * i + nargs) = glb;
3798 ARGT_ARG(argt, 3 * i + nargs + 1) = gub;
3799 ARGT_ARG(argt, 3 * i + nargs + 2) = mk_bnd_int(gst);
3800 if (gst == astb.bnd.one)
3801 strd1_cnt++;
3802 }
3803 nargs += 3 * ndim;
3804
3805 ARGT_ARG(argt, nargs++) = mk_isz_cval(sectflag | dim_mask, astb.bnd.dtype);
3806 if (size_of(DT_PTR) != size_of(DT_INT) && ndim <= 3) {
3807 /* for the hammer target, it's better to pass the
3808 * arguments to sect3 by ref ???? WHY ??? */
3809 switch (ndim) {
3810 case 3:
3811 fsptr = sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_sect3), DT_NONE);
3812 break;
3813 case 2:
3814 fsptr = sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_sect2), DT_NONE);
3815 break;
3816 case 1:
3817 fsptr = sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_sect1), DT_NONE);
3818 break;
3819 }
3820 } else if (ndim <= 3) {
3821 /* experiment with by value arguments */
3822 /* for the x86 target, it's better to pass the
3823 * arguments by value - makes sense!! */
3824 switch (ndim) {
3825 case 3:
3826 fsptr = sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_sect3v), DT_NONE);
3827 break;
3828 case 2:
3829 fsptr = sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_sect2v), DT_NONE);
3830 break;
3831 case 1:
3832 fsptr = sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_sect1v), DT_NONE);
3833 break;
3834 }
3835 for (i = 2; i < nargs; i++) {
3836 ARGT_ARG(argt, i) = mk_unop(OP_VAL, ARGT_ARG(argt, i), DT_INT);
3837 }
3838 } else {
3839 fsptr = sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_sect), DT_NONE);
3840 }
3841 astnew = mk_func_node(A_CALL, mk_id(fsptr), nargs, argt);
3842 NODESCP(A_SPTRG(A_LOPG(astnew)), 1);
3843
3844 std = add_stmt_before(astnew, std);
3845
3846 return sec;
3847}
3848
3849/** \brief Create a RTE_template call
3850 for an effective argument `a(1:n,3:m)`
3851
3852 Create a template that looks like `(1:n,1:m-2)`.
3853 Return sptr of the template we create.
3854 \p ast must be an A_SUBSCR that has a section subscript
3855 RTE_template (template, rank, flags, type, kind, [lb, ub,]... )
3856 */
3857int
3858make_simple_template_from_ast(int ast, int std, LOGICAL need_type_in_descr)
3859{
3860 int asd, numdim, sptr;
3861 int shape, sec, shapedim, descr;
3862 int nargs, cargs, argt, astnew;
3863 int i, j;
3864 int fsptr, dtype;
3865
3866 /* find the array that has the section */
3867 assert(ast > 0, "make_simple_template_from_ast: bad ast value", ast, 4);
3868 assert(A_TYPEG(ast) == A_SUBSCR,
3869 "make_simple_template_from_ast: expecting subscr", A_TYPEG(ast), 4);
3870
3871 asd = A_ASDG(ast);
3872 numdim = ASD_NDIM(asd);
3873 sptr = sptr_of_subscript(ast);
3874 if (is_whole_array(ast)) {
3875 /* if this is the whole array, just use the descriptor we have */
3876 DESCUSEDP(sptr, 1);
3877 return DESCRG(sptr);
3878 }
3879 shape = A_SHAPEG(ast);
3880 assert(shape > 0, "make_simple_template_from_ast: null shape", 0, 4);
3881 /* create a section descriptor */
3882 shapedim = SHD_NDIM(shape);
3883 sec = sym_get_sdescr(sptr, shapedim);
3884 /* RTE_template (template, rank, kind, len, flags, [lb, ub,]... ) */
3885 if (ASSUMSHPG(sptr) && XBIT(57, 0x10000)) {
3886 DESCUSEDP(sptr, 1);
3887 descr = DESCRG(sptr);
3888 }
3889 if (flg.smp && SCG(sec) != SC_PRIVATE && !PARREFG(sec)) {
3890 set_parref_flag2(sec, 0, std);
3891 }
3892 nargs = 5 + 2 * shapedim;
3893 cargs = 0;
3894 argt = mk_argt(nargs);
3895 ARGT_ARG(argt, cargs++) = mk_id(sec);
3896 ARGT_ARG(argt, cargs++) = mk_isz_cval(shapedim, astb.bnd.dtype);
3897 ARGT_ARG(argt, cargs++) = mk_isz_cval(0, astb.bnd.dtype);
3898 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
3899 dtype = DTY(dtype + 1);
3900 ARGT_ARG(argt, cargs++) = mk_isz_cval(dtype_to_arg(dtype), astb.bnd.dtype);
3901 ARGT_ARG(argt, cargs++) = size_of_dtype(dtype, sptr, ast);
3902 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
3903 assert(numdim == rank_of(dtype),
3904 "make_simple_template_from_ast: numdim/ndim mismatch asd", sptr, 4);
3905 j = 0;
3906 for (i = 0; i < numdim; ++i) {
3907 int ss, glb, gub, gst;
3908 ss = ASD_SUBS(asd, i);
3909 if (A_TYPEG(ss) == A_TRIPLE) {
3910 assert(j < shapedim, "make_simple_template_from_ast: SHD/ASD mismatch",
3911 shapedim, 4);
3912 glb = SHD_LWB(shape, j);
3913 gub = SHD_UPB(shape, j);
3914 gst = mk_bnd_int(SHD_STRIDE(shape, j));
3915 assert(gst == astb.bnd.one,
3916 "make_simple_template_from_ast: nonunit stride", gst, 4);
3917 glb = mk_bnd_int(glb);
3918 gub = mk_bnd_int(gub);
3919 if (ASSUMSHPG(sptr) && XBIT(57, 0x10000)) {
3920 /* offset by difference between actual/dummy lower bounds */
3921 glb = diff_lbnd(dtype, i, glb, descr);
3922 gub = diff_lbnd(dtype, i, gub, descr);
3923 }
3924 ARGT_ARG(argt, cargs++) = astb.bnd.one;
3925 ARGT_ARG(argt, cargs++) = mk_binop(OP_ADD, mk_binop(OP_SUB,
3926 gub, glb, astb.bnd.dtype),
3927 astb.bnd.one, astb.bnd.dtype);
3928 ++j;
3929 }
3930 }
3931
3932 fsptr = sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_template), DT_NONE);
3933 astnew = mk_func_node(A_CALL, mk_id(fsptr), nargs, argt);
3934 SDSCINITP(sec, 1);
3935 NODESCP(fsptr, 1);
3936 add_stmt_before(astnew, std);
3937
3938 if (need_type_in_descr)
3939 set_type_in_descriptor(mk_id(sec), sptr, DT_NONE, ast, std);
3940
3941 return sec;
3942}

3946{
3947 ADSC *ad;
3948 int dtype;
3949 int i;
3950 int ast1, ast2;
3951 int std;
3952 int newarg, newdsc;
3953 int astnew, present;
3954
3955#if DEBUG
3956 assert(STYPEG(arg) == ST_ARRAY, "set_assumed_dim: arg not array", arg, 4);
3957 assert(ASUMSZG(arg), "set_assumsz_bound: arg not assumed size", arg, 4);
3958#endif
3959 dtype = DTYPEG(arg);
3960 ad = AD_DPTR(dtype);
3961 std = ENTSTDG(entry);
3962
3963 newarg = NEWARGG(arg);

3965 assert(newarg && newdsc, "set_assumsz_bounds: needs newarg", newarg, 3);
3966

3968 if (OPTARGG(arg) && !f77_local) {

3970 present = ast_intr(I_PRESENT, stb.user.dt_log, 1, mk_id(newarg));
3971

3973 A_IFEXPRP(astnew, present);
3974 std = add_stmt_after(astnew, std);
3975 }
3976

3978 i = AD_NUMDIM(ad) - 1;

3986 std = add_stmt_after(ast2, std);
3987 /* if it is optional dummy */
3988 if (OPTARGG(arg) && !f77_local) {
3989 astnew = mk_stmt(A_ENDIF, 0);
3990 std = add_stmt_after(astnew, std);
3991 }
3992 ENTSTDP(entry, std);
3993}

3995static bool
3996update_shape_info_expr(int arg, int ast)
3997{
3998 int i;
3999 int aptr, sptr, shd = 0, nd;
4000
4001 switch (A_TYPEG(ast)) {
4002 case A_SUBSCR:
4003 aptr = (int)A_LOPG(ast);
4004 sptr = A_SPTRG(aptr);
4005 if (sptr == arg) {
4006 if ((shd = A_SHAPEG(aptr))) {
4007 nd = SHD_NDIM(shd);
4008 for (i = 0; i < nd; ++i)
4009 SHD_LWB(shd, i) = astb.bnd.one;
4010 return true;
4011 }
4012 }
4013 return false;
4014 break;
4015 case A_UNOP:
4016 case A_CONV:
4017 case A_PAREN:
4018 if (update_shape_info_expr(arg, A_LOPG(ast)))
4019 return true;
4020 break;
4021 case A_BINOP:
4022 if (update_shape_info_expr(arg, A_LOPG(ast)))
4023 return true;
4024 if (update_shape_info_expr(arg, A_ROPG(ast)))
4025 return true;
4026 break;
4027 default:
4028 break;
4029 }
4030 return false;
4031}
4032
4033static void
4034update_shape_info(int arg)
4035{
4036 int std, ast, dst, aptr, sptr;
4037 int i, nd, shd = 0;
4038
4039 for (std = STD_NEXT(0); std; std = STD_NEXT(std)) {
4040 ast = STD_AST(std);
4041 if (A_TYPEG(ast) != A_ASN && !A_ISEXPR(A_TYPEG(ast)))
4042 continue;
4043 dst = A_DESTG(ast);
4044 if (A_TYPEG(dst) != A_SUBSCR)
4045 continue;
4046 aptr = (int)A_LOPG(dst);
4047 sptr = A_SPTRG(aptr);
4048 if (sptr != arg) {
4049 if (update_shape_info_expr(arg, A_SRCG(ast)))
4050 return;
4051 continue;
4052 }
4053
4054 if ((shd = A_SHAPEG(aptr))) {
4055 nd = SHD_NDIM(shd);
4056 for (i = 0; i < nd; ++i)
4057 SHD_LWB(shd, i) = astb.bnd.one;
4058 return; /* found match and adjustment made */
4059 }
4060 }
4061}
4062
4063void
4064set_assumed_bounds(int arg, int entry, int actual)
4065{
4066 ADSC *ad;
4067 int dtype;
4068 int r;
4069 int i;
4070 int ast, ast1, ast2;
4071 int sav = 0;
4072 int tmp_lb, tmp_ub;
4073 int std;
4074 int newarg, newdsc;
4075 int astnew, present, zbaseast, prevmpyer;
4076
4077 assert(is_array_type(arg), "set_assumed_bounds: arg not array", 0, 4);
4078 dtype = DTYPEG(arg);
4079 ad = AD_DPTR(dtype);
4080 assert(AD_DEFER(ad), "set_assumed_bounds: arg not deferred", arg, 4);
4081 std = ENTSTDG(entry);
4082 r = AD_NUMDIM(ad);
4083
4084 newarg = NEWARGG(arg);
4085 newdsc = NEWDSCG(arg);
4086 /* OPTIONAL arg may not have newarg */
4087 if (OPTARGG(arg) && newarg == 0)
4088 return;
4089 assert(newarg && newdsc, "set_assumed_bounds: needs newarg", newarg, 3);
4090
4091 /* if is optional dummy */
4092 if (OPTARGG(arg) && !f77_local) {
4093 present = sym_mkfunc_nodesc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_present), stb.user.dt_log);
4094 present = ast_intr(I_PRESENT, stb.user.dt_log, 1,
4095 check_member(actual, mk_id(newarg)));
4096 astnew = mk_stmt(A_IFTHEN, 0);
4097 A_IFEXPRP(astnew, present);
4098 std = add_stmt_after(astnew, std);
4099 }
4100
4101 zbaseast = 0;
4102 prevmpyer = 0;
4103
4104 /* did we not set lower bound to 1 in to_assumed_shape() or
4105 * mk_assumed_shape() because TARGET was not yet available
4106 * (still in parser) when this xbit was set?
4107 */
4108 if (XBIT(58, 0x400000) && !TARGETG(arg)) {
4109 for (i = 0; i < r; ++i) {
4110 if (AD_LWBD(ad, i) == AD_LWAST(ad, i)) {
4111 if (A_TYPEG(AD_LWBD(ad, i)) == A_ID) {
4112 /* add assignment std to set lb to 1 */
4113 ast = mk_stmt(A_ASN, 0);
4114 A_DESTP(ast, AD_LWBD(ad, i));
4115 A_SRCP(ast, astb.bnd.one);
4116 std = add_stmt_after(ast, std);
4117 }
4118 AD_LWBD(ad, i) = astb.bnd.one;
4119 AD_LWAST(ad, i) = astb.bnd.one;
4120 }
4121 }
4122 /* also, arg is assumed shape, and since !TARGET mark as stride 1 */
4123 SDSCS1P(arg, 1); /* see comment below regarding these xbits */
4124 if( XBIT(55,0x80) )
4125 update_shape_info(arg);
4126 }
4127
4128 for (i = 0; i < r; ++i) {
4129 tmp_lb = AD_LWAST(ad, i); /* temp for lower bound */
4130 /* declare it by changing the scope */
4131 if (A_TYPEG(tmp_lb) == A_ID) {
4132 IGNOREP(A_SPTRG(tmp_lb), 0);
4133 }
4134
4135 if ((ast1 = AD_LWBD(ad, i)) == 0)
4136 /* lower bound not specified */
4137 ast1 = mk_isz_cval(1, astb.bnd.dtype);
4138 if (A_TYPEG(tmp_lb) == A_CNST) {
4139 sav = tmp_lb;
4140 } else if ((XBIT(54, 2) || (XBIT(58, 0x400000) && TARGETG(arg))) &&
4141 tmp_lb == ast1 && A_TYPEG(tmp_lb) == A_ID) {
4142 /*
4143 FIX ME: setting the descriptor bounds to 1 here does not work since
4144 there can be other references (such as loop bounds) which use the
4145 symbolic lower bounds for each dimension.
4146 ast1 = mk_isz_cval(1, astb.bnd.dtype);
4147 sav = AD_LWAST(ad, i) = AD_LWBD(ad, i) = ast1;
4148 */
4149
4150 /* so we just assign the symbolic lower bound ID to 1 */
4151 ast1 = mk_isz_cval(1, astb.bnd.dtype);
4152 sav = ast1;
4153 ast2 = mk_stmt(A_ASN, 0);
4154 A_DESTP(ast2, tmp_lb);
4155 A_SRCP(ast2, ast1);
4156 std = add_stmt_after(ast2, std);
4157 } else if (tmp_lb != ast1) {
4158 /* output lower bound assignment */
4159 /* lb = <declared lower bound> */
4160 sav = ast1;
4161 ast2 = mk_stmt(A_ASN, 0);
4162 A_DESTP(ast2, tmp_lb);
4163 A_SRCP(ast2, ast1);
4164 std = add_stmt_after(ast2, std);
4165 }
4166
4167 /* no need for upper bounds for pointer dummys */
4168 if (POINTERG(arg))
4169 continue;
4170
4171 /* output upper bound assignment */
4172 ast2 = extent(arg, check_member(actual, mk_id(newdsc)), i);
4173 /* ub = lb - 1 + pghpf_extent(a, dim) */
4174 ast1 = mk_binop(
4175 OP_ADD,
4176 mk_binop(OP_SUB, ast1, mk_isz_cval(1, astb.bnd.dtype), astb.bnd.dtype),
4177 ast2, astb.bnd.dtype);
4178 ast2 = mk_stmt(A_ASN, 0);
4179 A_SRCP(ast2, ast1);
4180 tmp_ub = AD_UPAST(ad, i);
4181 A_DESTP(ast2, tmp_ub);
4182 /* declare it by changing the scope */
4183 if (A_TYPEG(tmp_ub) == A_ID) {
4184 IGNOREP(A_SPTRG(tmp_ub), 0);
4185 }
4186 std = add_stmt_after(ast2, std);
4187
4188 if (sav != astb.bnd.one) {
4189 int a;
4190 /* generate: if (ub < lb) then ub = lb - 1; */
4191 present = mk_binop(OP_LT, tmp_ub, tmp_lb, astb.bnd.dtype);
4192 astnew = mk_stmt(A_IFTHEN, 0);
4193 A_IFEXPRP(astnew, present);
4194 std = add_stmt_after(astnew, std);
4195
4196 ast2 = mk_stmt(A_ASN, 0);
4197 A_DESTP(ast2, tmp_ub);
4198 a = mk_binop(OP_SUB, tmp_lb, astb.bnd.one, astb.bnd.dtype);
4199 A_SRCP(ast2, a);
4200 std = add_stmt_after(ast2, std);
4201
4202 astnew = mk_stmt(A_ENDIF, 0);
4203 std = add_stmt_after(astnew, std);
4204 }
4205 {
4206 int tmp, nexttmp, ast;
4207 /* update ZBASE ast */
4208 if (XBIT(57, 0x10000)) {
4209 int astoff;
4210 int lb;
4211 /* account for difference between actual argument lower bound
4212 * and assumed-shape argument declared lower bound */
4213 ast = get_global_lower(newdsc, i);
4214 if (!XBIT(58, 0x40000000)) {
4215 astoff = get_section_offset(newdsc, i);
4216 ast = mk_binop(OP_ADD, astoff, ast, astb.bnd.dtype);
4217 }
4218 lb = ADD_LWBD(dtype, i);
4219 if (lb == 0 || A_ALIASG(lb)) {
4220 ISZ_T lbval;
4221 /* get the constant value, subtract one, subtract that from ss */
4222 if (lb == 0) {
4223 lbval = 1;
4224 } else {
4225 lb = mk_bnd_int(A_ALIASG(lb));
4226 lbval = get_isz_cval(A_SPTRG(lb));
4227 }
4228 if (lbval) {
4229 ast = mk_binop(OP_SUB, ast, mk_isz_cval(lbval, astb.bnd.dtype),
4230 astb.bnd.dtype);
4231 }
4232 } else {
4233 int lwast;
4234 lwast = ADD_LWAST(dtype, i);
4235 ast = mk_binop(OP_SUB, ast, lwast, astb.bnd.dtype);
4236 }
4237 if (prevmpyer) {
4238 ast = mk_binop(OP_MUL, ast, prevmpyer, astb.bnd.dtype);
4239 }
4240 } else {
4241 if (AD_ZBASE(ad)) {
4242 ast = mk_binop(OP_MUL, AD_LWAST(ad, i), AD_MLPYR(ad, i),
4243 astb.bnd.dtype);
4244 } else {
4245 ast = 0;
4246 }
4247 }
4248 if (i == 0 || zbaseast == 0) {
4249 zbaseast = ast;
4250 } else if (A_ALIASG(AD_ZBASE(ad)) == 0 && ast) {
4251 zbaseast = mk_binop(OP_ADD, zbaseast, ast, astb.bnd.dtype);
4252 }
4253
4254 if (XBIT(57, 0x10000)) {
4255 if (i < r - 1) {
4256 /* add assignment to multiplier temp for next dimension */
4257 nexttmp = AD_MLPYR(ad, i + 1);
4258 if (nexttmp && A_ALIASG(nexttmp) == 0) {
4259 int sstride;
4260 prevmpyer = get_local_multiplier(newdsc, i + 1);
4261 if (XBIT(58, 0x40000000)) {
4262 /* no multiply-by-section-stride */
4263 ast = prevmpyer;
4264 } else {
4265 sstride = get_section_stride(newdsc, i + 1);
4266 ast = mk_binop(OP_MUL, sstride, prevmpyer, astb.bnd.dtype);
4267 }
4268 ast = mk_assn_stmt(nexttmp, ast, astb.bnd.dtype);
4269 std = add_stmt_after(ast, std);
4270 } else {
4271 prevmpyer = nexttmp;
4272 }
4273 }
4274 } else {
4275 /* add assignment to multiplier temp for next dimension */
4276 tmp = AD_MLPYR(ad, i);
4277 nexttmp = AD_MLPYR(ad, i + 1);
4278 if (tmp && nexttmp && A_ALIASG(nexttmp) == 0) {
4279 if (AD_LWBD(ad, i) == astb.bnd.one)
4280 ast = astb.bnd.one;
4281 else
4282 ast = AD_LWAST(ad, i);
4283 ast = mk_mlpyr_expr(ast, AD_UPAST(ad, i), tmp);
4284 ast = mk_assn_stmt(nexttmp, ast, astb.bnd.dtype);
4285 std = add_stmt_after(ast, std);
4286 }
4287 prevmpyer = nexttmp;
4288 }
4289 }
4290 }
4291 if (XBIT(57, 0x10000)) {
4292 int ast;
4293 ast = get_xbase(newdsc);
4294 zbaseast = mk_binop(OP_ADD, zbaseast, ast, astb.bnd.dtype);
4295 }
4296 if (zbaseast && A_ALIASG(AD_ZBASE(ad)) == 0) {
4297 int tmp, ast;
4298 /* add assignment to zbase temp */
4299 tmp = AD_ZBASE(ad);
4300 ast = mk_assn_stmt(tmp, zbaseast, astb.bnd.dtype);
4301 std = add_stmt_after(ast, std);
4302 }
4303
4304 /* if it is optional dummy */
4305 if (OPTARGG(arg) && !f77_local) {
4306 astnew = mk_stmt(A_ENDIF, 0);
4307 std = add_stmt_after(astnew, std);
4308 }
4309
4310 ENTSTDP(entry, std);
4311}

4313static void
4314component_init_allocd_auto(int ast, int std)
4315{
4316 SPTR sptr = memsym_of_ast(ast);
4317 DTYPE dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
4318 DTYPE basedtype = DDTG(dtype);
4319
4320 if (get_struct_initialization_tree(basedtype) != 0 && !CCSYMG(sptr)) {
4321 SPTR prototype = get_dtype_init_template(basedtype);
4322 if (prototype > NOSYM) {
4323 int tast = mk_id(prototype);
4324 int dest = mk_id(sptr);
4325 int j, ndim = 0;
4326 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
4327 int shape = A_SHAPEG(ast);
4328 int indx[MAXDIMS];
4329 ndim = SHD_NDIM(shape);
4330 for (j = 0; j < ndim; j++) {
4331 int astdo = mk_stmt(A_DO, 0);
4332 indx[j] = mk_id(get_temp(astb.bnd.dtype));
4333 A_DOVARP(astdo, indx[j]);
4334 A_M1P(astdo, SHD_LWB(shape, j));
4335 A_M2P(astdo, SHD_UPB(shape, j));
4336 A_M3P(astdo, astb.i1);
4337 A_M4P(astdo, 0);
4338 add_stmt_before(astdo, std);
4339 }
4340 dest = mk_subscr(dest, indx, ndim, basedtype);
4341 }
4342 add_stmt_before(mk_assn_stmt(dest, tast, basedtype), std);
4343 while (ndim-- > 0) {
4344 int astdo = mk_stmt(A_ENDDO, 0);
4345 add_stmt_before(astdo, std);
4346 }
4347 }
4348 }
4349}

4351/** \brief Insert memory allocation code for a symbol.
4352 \param sptr symbol table index for the symbol
4353 \return true if \sptr is an array of derived type, and the caller must
4354 initialize its components (by calling component_init_allocd_auto
4355 after calling wrap_symbol for sptr)
4356 */
4357static bool
4358allocate_one_auto(int sptr)
4359{
4360 bool need_init = false;
4361
4362 if (ADJLENG(sptr))
4363 add_auto_len(sptr, EntryStd);
4364 if (DTY(DTYPEG(sptr)) == TY_ARRAY) {
4365 if (ADJARRG(sptr) || RUNTIMEG(sptr)) {
4366 add_auto_bounds(sptr, EntryStd);
4367 }
4368 if (!ALIGNG(sptr)
4369 ) {
4370 ADSC *ad;
4371 int r, i, ast, subscr[7];
4372 ad = AD_DPTR(DTYPEG(sptr));
4373 /* make the subscripts */
4374 r = AD_NUMDIM(ad);
4375 for (i = 0; i < r; ++i)
4376 subscr[i] = mk_triple(AD_LWAST(ad, i), AD_UPAST(ad, i), 0);
4377 ast = mk_id(sptr);
4378 mk_mem_allocate(ast, subscr, EntryStd, ast);
4379 if (DTYG(DTYPEG(sptr)) == TY_DERIVED) {
4380 need_init = true; // caller must initialize components
4381 dealloc_dt_auto(ast, sptr, ExitStd);
4382 } else {
4383 mk_mem_deallocate(ast, ExitStd);
4384 }
4385 }
4386 } else if (!POINTERG(sptr)) {
4387 if (ADJLENG(sptr)) {
4388 /* scalar adjustable length char string */
4389 mk_allocate_scalar(0, sptr, EntryStd);
4390 mk_deallocate_scalar(0, sptr, ExitStd);
4391 }
4392 }
4393 return need_init;
4394} /* allocate_one_auto */

4463int

4465{
4466 int i;
4467 int ndim;
4468 int subs[7];

4470 int arrdsc;
4471 int sdsc;
4472 int ins;
4473 int dtype;
4474
4475 arrdsc = DESCRG(sptr);
4476 assert(arrdsc && STYPEG(arrdsc) == ST_ARRDSC,
4477 "get_allobnds: have to be descriptor", sptr, 3);
4478 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
4479 sdsc = 0;

4481 if (ins)
4482 sdsc = INS_DESCR(ins);
4483 if (!sdsc)
4484 sdsc = SECDSCG(arrdsc);
4485 assert(sdsc, "get_allobnds: no section descriptor", sptr, 3);
4486 ndim = rank_of_sym(sptr);

4492 if (normalize_bounds(sptr))
4493 ub = add_lbnd(dtype, i, ub, ast);
4494 subs[i] = mk_triple(lb, ub, 0);
4495 }
4496 return mk_subscr(ast, subs, ndim, DTY(DTYPEG(sptr)));

4654#if defined(BND_ASSN_PRECEDES)
4655static int
4656bnd_assn_precedes(int lhs, int entryStd, int wh)
4657{
4658 /*
4659 * We're at a point in the prologue where a bounds temp will be used
4660 * and that the assignment to the temp has already been generated.
4661 * Determine if the assignment precedes this point -- if not, we'll
4662 * have to replicate the assignment (see f15414).
4663 *
4664 * 12/3/2008 NOTE: Currently, we're not using this method to solve
4665 * f15414; scanning the STDs at this point is a bit risky, plus I
4666 * don't like the idea of generating redundant assignments that we
4667 * probably cannot delete.
4668 * The solution is to first look for those automatic arrays whose
4669 * whose bounds can be written 'early' in transform_wrapup (see
4670 * the first loop over the symbol table). Nevertheless, I'm keeping
4671 * this function here (just in case) and using the macro BND_ASSN_PRECEDES
4672 * to guard its calls.
4673 */
4674 int aa, ss;
4675 int fnd = 0;
4676 for (ss = STD_PREV(entryStd); ss; ss = STD_PREV(ss)) {
4677 aa = STD_AST(ss);
4678 if (A_TYPEG(aa) == A_ASN && A_DESTG(aa) == lhs) {
4679 fnd = 1;
4680 break;
4681 }
4682 }
4683 fprintf(stderr, "%s %sFOUND%d\n", SYMNAME(A_SPTRG(lhs)), fnd ? "" : "NOT",
4684 wh);
4685 return fnd;
4686}

4689static void
4690add_auto_bounds(int sym, int entryStd)
4691{
4692 int dtype;
4693 ADSC *ad;
4694 int numdim;
4695 int i;
4696 int bnd;
4697 int ast;
4698 int tmp;
4699 int zbaseast, mlpyrast;
4700
4701 dtype = DTYPEG(sym);
4702 ad = AD_DPTR(dtype);
4703 numdim = AD_NUMDIM(ad);
4704 zbaseast = 0;
4705 mlpyrast = astb.bnd.one;
4706 /* NOTE: a bound is adjustable if its ast is non-zero and it is
4707 * not a constant or aliased constant.
4708 */
4709 for (i = 0; i < numdim; i++) {
4710 bnd = AD_LWBD(ad, i);
4711 tmp = AD_LWAST(ad, i);
4712 if (A_TYPEG(bnd) == A_ID && EARLYSPECG(A_SPTRG(bnd))) {
4713 ;
4714 } else if (bnd && A_ALIASG(tmp) == 0 && bnd != tmp) {
4715 if (A_VISITG(tmp) == 0) {
4716 ast = mk_assn_stmt(tmp, bnd, DT_INT);
4717 bnd = get_scalar_in_expr(bnd, EntryStd, FALSE);
4718 add_stmt_before(ast, entryStd);
4719 A_SRCP(ast, bnd);
4720 ast_visit(tmp, tmp);
4721 }
4722#if defined(BND_ASSN_PRECEDES)
4723 else if (!bnd_assn_precedes(tmp, entryStd, 0)) {
4724 }
4725#endif
4726 }
4727 bnd = AD_UPBD(ad, i);
4728 tmp = AD_UPAST(ad, i);
4729 if (A_TYPEG(bnd) == A_ID && EARLYSPECG(A_SPTRG(bnd))) {
4730 ;
4731 } else if (bnd && A_ALIASG(tmp) == 0 && bnd != tmp) {
4732 if (A_VISITG(tmp) == 0) {
4733 ast = mk_assn_stmt(tmp, bnd, DT_INT);
4734 bnd = get_scalar_in_expr(bnd, EntryStd, FALSE);
4735 add_stmt_before(ast, entryStd);
4736 A_SRCP(ast, bnd);
4737 ast_visit(tmp, tmp);
4738 }
4739#if defined(BND_ASSN_PRECEDES)
4740 else if (!bnd_assn_precedes(tmp, entryStd, 1)) {
4741 /*
4742 ast = mk_assn_stmt(tmp, bnd, DT_INT);
4743 bnd = get_scalar_in_expr(bnd, entryStd, FALSE);
4744 add_stmt_before(ast, entryStd);
4745 A_SRCP(ast, bnd);
4746 */
4747 }
4748#endif
4749 }
4750 tmp = AD_EXTNTAST(ad, i);
4751 bnd = mk_extent_expr(AD_LWAST(ad, i), AD_UPAST(ad, i));
4752 if (tmp && A_ALIASG(tmp) == 0 && tmp != bnd) {
4753 if (A_VISITG(tmp) == 0) {
4754 ast = mk_assn_stmt(tmp, bnd, DT_INT);
4755 bnd = get_scalar_in_expr(bnd, EntryStd, FALSE);
4756 add_stmt_before(ast, entryStd);
4757 A_SRCP(ast, bnd);
4758 ast_visit(tmp, tmp);
4759 }
4760#if defined(BND_ASSN_PRECEDES)
4761 else if (!bnd_assn_precedes(tmp, entryStd, 2)) {
4762 }
4763#endif
4764 }
4765 tmp = AD_MLPYR(ad, i);
4766 if (tmp && !A_ALIASG(tmp) && tmp != mlpyrast && A_TYPEG(tmp) == A_ID) {
4767 if (A_VISITG(tmp) == 0) {
4768 ast = mk_assn_stmt(tmp, mlpyrast, DT_INT);
4769 add_stmt_before(ast, entryStd);
4770 ast_visit(tmp, tmp);
4771 }
4772#if defined(BND_ASSN_PRECEDES)
4773 else if (!bnd_assn_precedes(tmp, entryStd, 3)) {
4774 }
4775#endif
4776 mlpyrast = tmp;
4777 }
4778 mlpyrast = mk_binop(OP_MUL, mlpyrast, AD_EXTNTAST(ad, i), astb.bnd.dtype);
4779 if (zbaseast == 0) {
4780 zbaseast =
4781 mk_binop(OP_MUL, AD_LWAST(ad, i), AD_MLPYR(ad, i), astb.bnd.dtype);
4782 } else {
4783 zbaseast = mk_binop(
4784 OP_ADD, zbaseast,
4785 mk_binop(OP_MUL, AD_LWAST(ad, i), AD_MLPYR(ad, i), astb.bnd.dtype),
4786 astb.bnd.dtype);
4787 }
4788 }
4789 tmp = AD_NUMELM(ad);
4790 if (tmp && !A_ALIASG(tmp) && tmp != mlpyrast && A_TYPEG(tmp) == A_ID) {
4791 if (A_VISITG(tmp) == 0) {
4792 ast = mk_assn_stmt(tmp, mlpyrast, DT_INT);
4793 add_stmt_before(ast, entryStd);
4794 ast_visit(tmp, tmp);
4795 }
4796#if defined(BND_ASSN_PRECEDES)
4797 else if (!bnd_assn_precedes(tmp, entryStd, 4)) {
4798 }
4799#endif
4800 }
4801 tmp = AD_ZBASE(ad);
4802 if (tmp && A_ALIASG(tmp) == 0 && tmp != zbaseast && A_TYPEG(tmp) == A_ID) {
4803 if (A_VISITG(tmp) == 0) {
4804 ast = mk_assn_stmt(tmp, zbaseast, astb.bnd.dtype);
4805 add_stmt_before(ast, entryStd);
4806 ast_visit(tmp, tmp);
4807 }
4808#if defined(BND_ASSN_PRECEDES)
4809 else if (!bnd_assn_precedes(tmp, entryStd, 5)) {
4810 }
4811#endif
4812 }
4813} /* add_auto_bounds */

4859
4860static int
4861get_scalar_in_expr(int expr, int std, LOGICAL astversion)
4862{
4863 int l, r, d, o;
4864 int l1, l2, l3;
4865 int i, nargs, argt;
4866
4867 if (expr == 0)
4868 return expr;
4869 switch (A_TYPEG(expr)) {
4870 /* expressions */
4871 case A_BINOP:
4872 o = A_OPTYPEG(expr);
4873 d = A_DTYPEG(expr);
4874 l = get_scalar_in_expr(A_LOPG(expr), std, astversion);
4875 r = get_scalar_in_expr(A_ROPG(expr), std, astversion);
4876 return mk_binop(o, l, r, d);
4877 case A_UNOP:
4878 o = A_OPTYPEG(expr);
4879 d = A_DTYPEG(expr);
4880 l = get_scalar_in_expr(A_LOPG(expr), std, astversion);
4881 return mk_unop(o, l, d);
4882 case A_CONV:
4883 d = A_DTYPEG(expr);
4884 l = get_scalar_in_expr(A_LOPG(expr), std, astversion);
4885 return mk_convert(l, d);
4886 case A_PAREN:
4887 d = A_DTYPEG(expr);
4888 l = get_scalar_in_expr(A_LOPG(expr), std, astversion);
4889 return mk_paren(l, d);
4890 case A_MEM:
4891 l = get_scalar_in_expr(A_PARENTG(expr), std, astversion);
4892 r = A_MEMG(expr);
4893 d = A_DTYPEG(r);
4894 return mk_member(l, r, d);
4895 case A_SUBSTR:
4896 d = A_DTYPEG(expr);
4897 l1 = get_scalar_in_expr(A_LOPG(expr), std, astversion);
4898 l2 = l3 = 0;
4899 if (A_LEFTG(expr))
4900 l2 = get_scalar_in_expr(A_LEFTG(expr), std, astversion);
4901 if (A_RIGHTG(expr))
4902 l3 = get_scalar_in_expr(A_RIGHTG(expr), std, astversion);
4903 return mk_substr(l1, l2, l3, d);
4904 case A_INTR:
4905 case A_FUNC:
4906 nargs = A_ARGCNTG(expr);
4907 argt = A_ARGSG(expr);
4908 for (i = 0; i < nargs; ++i) {
4909 ARGT_ARG(argt, i) =
4910 get_scalar_in_expr(ARGT_ARG(argt, i), std, astversion);
4911 }
4912 return expr;
4913 case A_CNST:
4914 case A_CMPLXC:
4915 case A_ID:
4916 return expr;
4917 case A_SUBSCR:
4918 if (astversion)
4919 expr = emit_get_scalar(expr, std);
4920 else
4921 expr = emit_get_scalar_sub(expr, std);
4922 return expr;
4923 case A_TRIPLE:
4924 l1 = get_scalar_in_expr(A_LBDG(expr), std, astversion);
4925 l2 = get_scalar_in_expr(A_UPBDG(expr), std, astversion);
4926 l3 = get_scalar_in_expr(A_STRIDEG(expr), std, astversion);
4927 return mk_triple(l1, l2, l3);
4928 default:
4929 interr("get_scalar_in_expr: unknown expression", expr, 2);
4930 return expr;
4931 }
4932}

4934static int
4935emit_get_scalar_sub(int a, int std)
4936{
4937 int l;
4938 int astnew;
4939 int i, nargs, argt;
4940 int asd;
4941 int ndim;
4942 int sptr, sptr1;
4943 int arrdsc;
4944 int secd;
4945 int descr, lop;
4946
4947 asd = A_ASDG(a);
4948 ndim = ASD_NDIM(asd);
4949 l = A_LOPG(a);
4950 sptr1 = sptr_of_subscript(a);
4951 if (!DISTG(sptr1) && !ALIGNG(sptr1))
4952 return a;
4953 /* It is distributed. Create a temp to hold the value */
4954 sptr = sym_get_scalar(SYMNAME(sptr1), "s", DTY(DTYPEG(sptr1) + 1));
4955 /* put out a call to fetch the value */
4956 /* call pghpf_get_scalar(temp, array_base, array, subscripts) */
4957
4958 arrdsc = DESCRG(sptr1);
4959 assert(arrdsc, "emit_get_scalar_sub: descriptor does not exist", sptr, 3);
4960 secd = SECDG(arrdsc);
4961 assert(secd, "emit_get_scalar_sub: descriptor does not exist", sptr, 3);
4962 descr = INS_DESCR(secd);
4963 assert(descr, "emit_get_scalar_sub: descriptor does not exist", sptr, 3);
4964 nargs = ndim + 3;
4965 argt = mk_argt(nargs);
4966 ARGT_ARG(argt, 0) = mk_id(sptr);
4967 ARGT_ARG(argt, 1) = mk_id(sptr1);
4968 ARGT_ARG(argt, 2) = mk_id(descr);
4969 DESCUSEDP(A_SPTRG(l), 1);
4970 for (i = 0; i < ndim; ++i) {
4971 astnew = mk_default_int(ASD_SUBS(asd, i));
4972 if (normalize_bounds(sptr1))
4973 astnew = sub_lbnd(DTYPEG(sptr1), i, astnew, a);
4974 ARGT_ARG(argt, i + 3) = astnew;
4975 }
4976 astnew = mk_stmt(A_CALL, 0);
4977 lop = mk_id(sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_get_scalar), DT_NONE));
4978 A_LOPP(astnew, lop);
4979 A_ARGCNTP(astnew, nargs);
4980 A_ARGSP(astnew, argt);
4981 add_stmt_before(astnew, std);
4982 report_comm(std, GETSCALAR_CAUSE);
4983 return mk_id(sptr);
4984}

4998/* look for A_ID for a OPTIONAL dummy parameter; make a
4999 * PRESENT(dummy) call; if there is more than one, .AND. the
5000 * tests together; I wrote this to handle the same AST types
5001 * handled in get_scalar_in_expr */
5002static void
5003find_presence(int ast, int *piftest)
5004{
5005 int nargs, argt, i, ndim, asd, sptr;
5006 if (ast == 0)
5007 return;
5008 switch (A_TYPEG(ast)) {
5009 /* expressions */
5010 case A_ID:
5011 sptr = A_SPTRG(ast);
5012 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY && OPTARGG(sptr)) {
5013 int iftest;
5014 if (NEWARGG(sptr)) {
5015 iftest = ast_intr(I_PRESENT, stb.user.dt_log, 1, mk_id(NEWARGG(sptr)));
5016 } else {
5017 iftest = ast_intr(I_PRESENT, stb.user.dt_log, 1, ast);
5018 }
5019 if (*piftest) {
5020 iftest = mk_binop(OP_LAND, iftest, *piftest, stb.user.dt_log);
5021 }
5022 *piftest = iftest;
5023 }
5024 break;
5025 case A_CNST:
5026 case A_CMPLXC:
5027 break;
5028 case A_BINOP:
5029 find_presence(A_LOPG(ast), piftest);
5030 find_presence(A_ROPG(ast), piftest);
5031 break;
5032 case A_UNOP:
5033 case A_CONV:
5034 case A_PAREN:
5035 find_presence(A_LOPG(ast), piftest);
5036 break;
5037 case A_MEM:
5038 find_presence(A_PARENTG(ast), piftest);
5039 break;
5040 case A_SUBSTR:
5041 find_presence(A_LOPG(ast), piftest);
5042 if (A_LEFTG(ast))
5043 find_presence(A_LEFTG(ast), piftest);
5044 if (A_RIGHTG(ast))
5045 find_presence(A_RIGHTG(ast), piftest);
5046 break;
5047 case A_INTR:
5048 case A_FUNC:
5049 nargs = A_ARGCNTG(ast);
5050 argt = A_ARGSG(ast);
5051 for (i = 0; i < nargs; ++i) {
5052 find_presence(ARGT_ARG(argt, i), piftest);
5053 }
5054 break;
5055 case A_SUBSCR:
5056 find_presence(A_LOPG(ast), piftest);
5057 asd = A_ASDG(ast);
5058 ndim = ASD_NDIM(asd);
5059 for (i = 0; i < ndim; ++i) {
5060 find_presence(ASD_SUBS(asd, i), piftest);
5061 }
5062 break;
5063 case A_TRIPLE:
5064 find_presence(A_LBDG(ast), piftest);
5065 find_presence(A_UPBDG(ast), piftest);
5066 find_presence(A_STRIDEG(ast), piftest);
5067 break;
5068 default:
5069 interr("find_presence: unknown expression", ast, 2);
5070 break;
5071 }
5072} /* find_presence */
5073
5074static int
5075add_presence(int ast, int std)
5076{
5077 int astpresent = 0;
5078 find_presence(ast, &astpresent);
5079 if (astpresent) {
5080 int astnew;
5081 astnew = mk_stmt(A_IFTHEN, 0);
5082 A_IFEXPRP(astnew, astpresent);
5083 add_stmt_before(astnew, std);
5084 }
5085 return astpresent;
5086} /* add_presence */
5087
5088static void
5089add_end_presence(int astpresent, int std)
5090{
5091 if (astpresent) {
5092 int astnew;
5093 astnew = mk_stmt(A_ENDIF, 0);
5094 add_stmt_before(astnew, std);
5095 }
5096} /* add_end_presence */

5098static void
5099add_bound_assignments(int sym)
5100{
5101 int dtype;
5102 ADSC *ad;
5103 int numdim;
5104 int i;
5105 int bnd;
5106 int ast;
5107 int tmp;
5108 int zbaseast;
5109 int astpresent;
5110 int isfval;
5111 int std, adjstd;
5112 int entryStd = EntryStd;
5113
5114 isfval = this_entry_fval == sym;
5115
5116 dtype = DTYPEG(sym);
5117 ad = AD_DPTR(dtype);
5118 numdim = AD_NUMDIM(ad);
5119
5120 adjstd = 0;
5121 zbaseast = 0;
5122 /* NOTE: a bound is adjustable if its ast is non-zero and it is
5123 * not a constant or aliased constant.
5124 */
5125 for (i = 0; i < numdim; i++) {
5126 bnd = AD_LWBD(ad, i);
5127 tmp = AD_LWAST(ad, i);
5128 if (bnd && !A_ALIASG(tmp) && !EARLYSPECG(A_SPTRG(tmp)) && tmp != bnd) {
5129 if (A_VISITG(tmp) == 0) {
5130 astpresent = add_presence(bnd, entryStd);
5131 ast = mk_assn_stmt(tmp, bnd, astb.bnd.dtype);
5132 bnd = get_scalar_in_expr(bnd, entryStd, FALSE);
5133 A_SRCP(ast, bnd);
5134 std = add_stmt_before(ast, entryStd);
5135 add_end_presence(astpresent, entryStd);
5136 ast_visit(tmp, tmp); /* mark id ast as visited */
5137 }
5138 }
5139 bnd = AD_UPBD(ad, i);
5140 tmp = AD_UPAST(ad, i);
5141 if (bnd && !A_ALIASG(tmp) && !EARLYSPECG(A_SPTRG(tmp)) && tmp != bnd) {
5142 if (A_VISITG(tmp) == 0) {
5143 astpresent = add_presence(bnd, entryStd);
5144 ast = mk_assn_stmt(tmp, bnd, astb.bnd.dtype);
5145 bnd = get_scalar_in_expr(bnd, entryStd, FALSE);
5146 A_SRCP(ast, bnd);
5147 std = add_stmt_before(ast, entryStd);
5148 add_end_presence(astpresent, entryStd);
5149 ast_visit(tmp, tmp); /* mark id ast as visited */
5150 }
5151 }
5152 bnd = mk_extent_expr(AD_LWAST(ad, i), AD_UPAST(ad, i));
5153 tmp = AD_EXTNTAST(ad, i);
5154 if (bnd && A_ALIASG(tmp) == 0) {
5155 if (A_VISITG(tmp) == 0) {
5156 astpresent = add_presence(bnd, entryStd);
5157 ast = mk_assn_stmt(tmp, bnd, astb.bnd.dtype);
5158 bnd = get_scalar_in_expr(bnd, entryStd, FALSE);
5159 A_SRCP(ast, bnd);
5160 std = add_stmt_before(ast, entryStd);
5161 add_end_presence(astpresent, entryStd);
5162 }
5163 ast_visit(tmp, tmp); /* mark id ast as visited */
5164 }
5165 {
5166 /* update the ZBASE ast tree */
5167 int nexttmp, ast;
5168 if (i == 0) {
5169 zbaseast = AD_LWAST(ad, i);
5170 } else if (A_ALIASG(AD_ZBASE(ad)) == 0) {
5171 int a;
5172 a = mk_binop(OP_MUL, AD_LWAST(ad, i), AD_MLPYR(ad, i), astb.bnd.dtype);
5173 zbaseast = mk_binop(OP_ADD, zbaseast, a, astb.bnd.dtype);
5174 }
5175 /* add assignment to multiplier temp for next dimension */
5176 tmp = AD_MLPYR(ad, i);
5177 nexttmp = AD_MLPYR(ad, i + 1);
5178 if (tmp && nexttmp && A_ALIASG(nexttmp) == 0 && A_VISITG(nexttmp) == 0) {
5179 if (AD_LWBD(ad, i) == astb.bnd.one)
5180 ast = astb.bnd.one;
5181 else
5182 ast = AD_LWAST(ad, i);
5183 ast = mk_mlpyr_expr(ast, AD_UPAST(ad, i), tmp);
5184 ast = mk_assn_stmt(nexttmp, ast, astb.bnd.dtype);
5185 std = add_stmt_before(ast, entryStd);
5186 if (!adjstd)
5187 adjstd = std;
5188 ast_visit(nexttmp, nexttmp); /* mark id ast as visited */
5189 }
5190 }
5191 }
5192 if (A_ALIASG(AD_ZBASE(ad)) == 0) {
5193 /* add assignment to zbase temp */
5194 tmp = AD_ZBASE(ad);
5195 if (A_VISITG(tmp) == 0) {
5196 ast = mk_assn_stmt(tmp, zbaseast, astb.bnd.dtype);
5197 std = add_stmt_before(ast, entryStd);
5198 ast_visit(tmp, tmp); /* mark id ast as visited */
5199 }
5200 }
5201}

5203/**
5204 * If the symbol is pointer-based, need to make sure that the storage class
5205 * of its descriptor is consistent with its pointer; specifically (f15624),
5206 * if the pointer is SC_PRIVATE, the descriptor must be SC_PRIVATE.
5207 * Generally speaking, privatizing temps occurs at the time the temps are
5208 * created. Context is set wrt being in a parallel region. Unfortunately,
5209 * the parallel vs serial context is not available at transform_wrapup-time
5210 * where the only information available is what's in the symbol table. The
5211 * routine used to create descriptors is via symutl.c:trans_mkdescr(). This
5212 * routine is called from various points in the compiler and creates ST_ARRDSC
5213 * entries which eventually become ...$sd temp arrays. The bug of f15624 has
5214 * to do with the descriptors of the temps created for copy-in/copy-out calls
5215 * at certain call sites.
5216 * REVISION - the private storage class cannot simply be copied to the
5217 * descriptor; a private allocatable array will have a shared descriptor.
5218 */
5219static void
5220fix_sdsc_sc(int sptr, int sdsc, int arrdsc)
5221{
5222 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_BASED) {
5223 if (SCG(arrdsc) == SC_PRIVATE) {
5224 SCP(sdsc, SC_PRIVATE);
5225 }
5226 }
5227}
